title: reduced calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatine in 1/3 cup milk; let set 1 minute.
Heat in microwave on High about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until dissolved.
Add remaining milk to dissolved mixture.
Add pumpkin and spice. Blend well.
Place mixture over ice water and stir until mixture starts to thicken.
Pour into diet crust.
Chill until firm. Nutrient Exchange: 1/3 milk, 1/4 bread and 1/4 meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage slaw
directions: Place cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce and garlic.
Pour over cabbage, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill about 1 hour, stirring once or twice.

title: jim's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together with mixer; make into roll.
Roll in dried chip beef or chopped ham.
Serve on crackers of your choice.

title: little cranberry meat loaves
directions: Combine meat with rice, tomato juice, egg, minced onion, Kitchen Bouquet and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape meat mixture into 5 individual loaves.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. For topping, combine cranberry sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Spoon over loaves.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove loaves to warm serving platter.
Pour cranberry sauce from pan; pass with meat loaves.
Yields 5 servings.
Bon Appetit!

title: granny isley's old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over crumbled biscuits, enough to cover biscuits, and let stand.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Add to biscuit mixture.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch dish or round pie pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peppar kakor(swedish ginger cookie)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Place dough on waxed paper into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Chill well.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices and place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: doneen's stuffed chili peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers. Mix beaten egg and cheese. Stuff peppers with cheese and egg mixture and place in electric skillet. Top with tomato sauce and cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: cheese logs
directions: Grind together Cheddar and cream cheese, pimiento and almonds; stir in lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire and onion.
Shape into logs about 1 1/4-inch in diameter; roll in diced almonds.
Chill. Slice thin to serve.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy with 1 cup milk in double boiler, stirring to mix well.
Cool.
Combine with condensed milk, chocolate syrup and 11 cups milk in 1-gallon ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: crinkle sunflower cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in well-greased tube pan or in loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cashew topping
directions: Blend cashews and arrowroot with hot water, then put in a saucepan and add vanilla and salt.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and use as a topping for pie, etc.
Fold in blended or finely chopped dried fruit such as apricots, apples, dates, etc. to make topping for waffles or French toast.
May be used like whipped cream.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook
and
drain raisins.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, eggs, sour cream and raisins.	Boil until thick, stirring constantly.	Pour over
crumb
mixture.
Sprinkle
some of mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Put pineapple and juice in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Smooth over top and add melted margarine.
Bake at 350°
until brown.
Cut in squares.
Serve with ice cream on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 40 minutes or until set.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter.
Saute garlic; do not let it get brown. Add juice from clams.
Add parsley; let simmer.
Boil water for linguini; cook linguini.
After linguini is cooked, take 1 cup linguini water and add to sauce; at this time also add clams. When pasta is cooked, mix in a bowl.
Add sauce, then some cheese, then add linguini, making a layer effect.
Toss and enjoy!

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Stir in half of the dry ingredients.
Add cherry juice and milk; mix well.
Stir in remaining dry ingredients and mix.
Blend in chopped nuts and cherries.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Do not stir anymore until ready to drop into deep fryer.
Drop by teaspoons into deep fryer.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Remove and drain.
Serve.

title: capers-spinach salad
directions: Wash mushrooms, drain, dry and slice thinly.
Mix oil, vinegar, capers, pimiento, cayenne, salt and pepper.
Pour over mushrooms, tossing gently to mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or more.
Wash spinach carefully, removing all sand and grit.
Pull off tough stems and discard. Dry leaves. Divide spinach among 4 salad bowls or plates.
Sprinkle marinated mushrooms evenly over spinach.
Divide the tuna evenly among the plates at this time if desired. Garnish each with a pepper ring.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an air-tight container.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over melted butter in baking dish, then pour in the sweetened peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: cazuela sabrosa
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in a little oil over low heat, stirring often, until limp.
Oil a shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix next 7 ingredients together.

Dot with Neufchatel, sprinkle with shredded cheese, cover and refrigerate until needed. When ready to bake, set in a preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 375° and bake 55 minutes or until macaroni tests tender with a fork.
If baking at once use a temperature of 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, oats, milk, onion, pepper and salt; mix well. Shape into about 30 small meatballs. Brown in melted (hot) shortening. Drain.

title: my sister's chocolate pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed for pie.
Put in crust and cool. Pile cherry pie filling in center of crust and edge with Cool Whip.

title: egg noodles
directions: Stir egg.
Add 1/2 egg shell of milk and add salt and 2 drops of yellow food coloring.
Stir in enough flour to make a dough. Roll out on floured surface.
Cut in thin strips and let dry. Freezes very good!

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend and mix well the first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch lightly buttered pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of mixture.
Spread out to cover entire dish.
Press cake mix in mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix.
Press nuts slightly.
Drizzle with butter, melted.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: nana's lemon chicken
directions: Mix cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip cutlets in egg and then bread and cheese mix.
Fry in oil until brown.
Remove chicken from pan and drain oil.
Mix water and flour.
Put in pan and add water, if needed.
Add juice of 1/2 lemon.
Replace cutlets and simmer 15 minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fluffy biscuits
directions: Combine boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and let cool.
Add eggs, then sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water. Stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Blend in flour. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Shape, using only enough flour for easy handling.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and allow to rise for 3 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions and cool completely. Combine Cool Whip, sour cream and strawberries (do not use juice from frozen berries).
Add 1/2 box confectioners sugar and beat together.
Add a few drops of red food color to make pretty.
Add icing to cake.
Garnish with berries.
Keep in refrigerator. Enjoy.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Brown stew meat in oil; add onions.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups. Stir mushrooms and liquid into meat and onions.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: herring-stuffed beets
directions: With small melon scoop, hollow out top of each beet.
Drain and coarsely chop herring and fill each beet with 1/2 teaspoon. Dot with sour cream and garnish with dill weed sprigs.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bob hall's southwest corn and pepper chowder
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients, except cream.
Heat over low flame, slowly folding in cream.
Do not boil.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, egg and onions.
Stir well. Drop by tablespoons into enough hot oil to cover. Cook only a few at a time. Turn once. Fry until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well on paper towels.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen. Serve hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli, then spread into a large casserole dish (I use 13 x 9-inch size).
Spread the cooked and cut up chicken evenly over the broccoli.
In a large bowl, mix the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Blend well and spread over chicken and broccoli.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
About 10 minutes before you take it out, sprinkle the shredded cheese on top and let it finish cooking.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crumb crust.
Top with strawberry or blueberry pie filling.

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pare off narrow strip of peel around center of each.
Cook in boiling, salted water until done, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain.
Meanwhile, cook fresh peas and onion in small amount boiling salted water, 8 to 15 minutes; drain.

title: seven grain bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
After proofing yeast, mix in 2 cups warm water, brown sugar or honey, salt and vegetable oil.
Add seven grain flour and enough white flour to make firm dough.
Knead well.
Let rise 2 times.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soup, water, pork and beans and seasoning.
Heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
While the mixture is heating, mix the cornbread and let stand 5 minutes. Then drop by tablespoon onto beans and hamburger, making 6 or 7 mounds on top.
Cover; cook until cornbread is done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
(For sheet cake, bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 1 hour.)
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and then remove and cool completely.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix the cream cheese and brown sugar.
Add the flavorings and blend well.
Serve with fruit.

title: chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: celestial crusts
directions: Mix cream, milk and unbeaten egg yolks.
Sift flour with sugar and salt.
Add liquid.
Form dough into balls the size of 1/2 walnut.
Roll very thin on floured board to almost size of a saucer.
Slit 4 times.
Fry in deep fat 395°, turning once. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: slosh
directions: Whip eggs and milk together.
Soak cubed bread 10 minutes. Add meat, onion, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes until firm and sprinkle with paprika.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cocoa and eggs.
Mix together good, then add vanilla, milk and zucchini.
Mix good, stirring with spoon. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 bread pans.

title: savory southern stuffing
directions: Cook sausage, stirring until brown; drain.
Melt margarine. Add onion and celery; saute until tender.
Stir in poultry seasoning.
Combine corn bread, herb stuffing, pecans, sausage and onion mixture.
Beat eggs and broth and pour over mixture, tossing gently.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chili burgers
directions: Cut dried beef into pieces and rinse with boiling water. Drain and add chili sauce.
Put on split hamburger buns.
Broil for 3 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and broil another 3 minutes.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine 1 stick melted butter, vanilla wafers and 1/2 cup powdered sugar; mix and place in bottom of oblong cake dish.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt 5 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Saute leek until soft and golden.
Add pumpkin, chicken stock and salt.
Bring to a boil stirring, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Put the soup through a sieve or ricer.
Return the soup to the pan.
Mix the flour with 3 tablespoons butter; gradually add to the soup while beating with a whisk.
Bring to boil, whisking until thick.
Taste and season, then add cream and remaining butter.
Serve with croutons.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Slice sausages and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nut fudge(very good for christmas candy)
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, oleo, marshmallows or marshmallow cream, salt and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate until melted.
Stir in broken nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into about 30 pieces.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix chicken and Cheddar cheese.
Divide this mixture into 8 equal portions.
Place on crescent roll section, roll up and place in baking dish.
Stir-fry the 2 cups of vegetables in skillet until tender.
Mix skim milk, water, poultry seasoning, chicken broth seasoning and cornstarch together.
Add this mixture to vegetables.
Stir until thickened.
Add Velveeta cheese.
When cheese is melted, pour this mixture over crescent rolls and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: irish coffee(microwave)
directions: Pour Irish whiskey into a mug.
Add water.
Stir in coffee and sugar.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until steaming.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 1 serving.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion seasoned with salt and pepper; drain fat. Combine all other ingredients.
Blend in with meat and cheeses. Grease casserole dish or 9 1/2-inch pan and put a layer of sauce, layer of noodles, etc., until all is used.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Excellent meal to freeze and cook on short notice.

title: york peppermint patty brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, stir together oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend well.

title: meat balls in chili gravy
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk, meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls.
Brown balls in shortening.
Mix chili sauce, water, celery, horseradish and lemon juice.
Pour sauce over meat balls.
Cook covered 20 minutes, stirring and turning balls in sauce.
Beef, veal, lamb or lean pork can be used but beef is best.

title: lynn's squash casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with small amount of herb dressing.
Top with squash mixture, then top with remaining herb dressing.
Dot with margarine.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: texas beans
directions: Cook pinto beans.
Brown ground beef.
Add all ingredients and simmer one hour.
Add beans and simmer an additional hour.

title: crazy custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a glass pie pan.
Mix ingredients in mixer or blender.
Pour in pan.
Cook until brown. Remove from oven and let cool slightly to set.
Good served warm or cold.

title: crunchy turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Make batter from dry ingredients and add the eggs.
Add zucchini, onion and cheese.
Stir well.
Drop by tablespoon in skillet with oleo.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: devil's food delight
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil, butter, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add buttermilk with soda last.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: minted lime soda
directions: To each of 6 chilled, 12 ounce glasses, add 1 tablespoon of creme de menthe syrup and 1 tablespoon of the lime juice.
To each glass add a small amount of the ice cream and 1/2 cup of the carbonated beverage.
Stir to muddle.
Place additional scoops of ice cream in glasses; fill with remaining carbonated beverage. Garnish with mint sprigs.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until center sets.

title: italian salad
directions: Put everything together and put in refrigerator overnight. Be sure to toss.

title: a zippy tomato drink
directions: *BLKLIN and 1/4 teaspoon oregano for spinach, carrots, zucchini, broccoli, beets or lima beans.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Put all ingredients in stew pan and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with hot corn bread and a salad.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
As pudding thickens, fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crackers and pudding starting and ending the crackers in a casserole dish.
Mix 4 tablespoons milk with can of frosting.
Spread over cake and cool.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all above ingredients together with just enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Chill 2 or 3 hours or overnight.

title: palacsintas
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Combine well beaten egg and milk. Add gradually to flour mixture, beating to a thin smooth batter. Spoon 3 tablespoons of batter on hot buttered greased skillet (will be very thin).
Brown lightly on both sides.
Continue until batter is used.
Spread cottage cheese.
Top with strawberry preserves and sour cream.

title: inexpensive sponge cake
directions: Beat until light and fluffy eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Put butter in hot milk.
Beat in above mixture.
Add baking powder into mixture and mix quickly.
Cool.
Cut in half for 2 layers.
Add instant lemon pudding for 2 boxes.
Use 3 cups milk.
Spread between layers.
Frost with white or lemon creme frosting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fry O'Brien potatoes with salt and pepper.
Layer on top of sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Pour egg on top.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and continue to cream. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating between additions. Add sifted flour. Mix well. Add extracts. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini special
directions: Layer vegetables in a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and lay cheese slices on top of veggies.
Bake until cheese melts, a very few minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put the stick of butter in a pan in cold oven.
Then, turn oven on to 350° and melt butter.
Mix 1 cup of milk with dry ingredients.
Add the 1/2 cup milk and mix.
Pour batter over the melted butter.
Spoon pie filling (any kid of fruit pie filling; your choice) on top of batter.
The batter will rise and surround the fruit.
Bake 35 minutes.
To test for doneness, pat on corners and the middle.
If the jiggle is the same, it is done.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, mix together ground beef, salt, garlic, oregano, chopped onion, spread smooth in pan.
Top with corn.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When done, cut into squares.
Top with potatoes and brown gravy.

title: glazed ham balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Mix lightly, but well.
Shape into 40 meatballs (1 1/2-inch).
Place in a single layer in shallow pan.
In bowl, mix together remaining ingredients and pour over the meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Spoon meatballs into serving dish.
Skim fat from sauce and pour sauce over the meatballs.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind shrimp, onions, jalapenos, lemon juice and cream cheese with mixer.
Add shrimp mixture; add mayonnaise to right consistency.
Optional:
Celery could be added and more jalapenos.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Trim ends of mushrooms and wash quickly.
Cut mushrooms in half.
Place in pan, bring to a boil and blanch for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Drain and combine with remaining ingredients.
Add dressing and stir often, marinating overnight in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package. Drain well. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Melt cheese; add raw sausage and Bisquick mix.
Mix well. Make small balls, put on greased cookie sheet and flatten a little.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine until lightly browned.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions until transparent. Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually stir into flour mixture in skillet.
Blend in evaporated milk until smooth.
Add mushrooms.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook slowly until onions, tomatoes and peppers are done.
Stir often and put in jars and seal.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Season veal with black pepper and garlic.
Rub cheese on both sides of cutlets.
Melt margarine in a Teflon frying pan; saute veal for about 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buns for hot dogs and hamburgers
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, margarine, sugar, salt, egg and 2 cups flour; beat well for 2 minutes.
Beat in remaining flour by hand to make a soft dough. Knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; roll out on floured surface 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into desired size and shape. Put on greased cookie sheet; let rise until double in bulk again. Brush with water; sprinkle
with sesame or poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: judy's mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa; remove from heat.
Cool; stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla; mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
Put marshmallows on hot cake (about 3/4 bag).
Cover with Chocolate Butter Frosting.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in tube pan for 1 hour.

title: potato cakes
directions: Prepare potato as on package; let it cool.
Combine cheese, crumbs, egg, parsley, onion and salt with potato; heat the oil in a skillet.
Form small round patties of potato mixture.
Fry in skillet on both sides, 4 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small chunks.
Mix chicken and other ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Cover with buttered crumbs or Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: mint brownies
directions: Prepare brownies by mixing ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: ma beaudries sugar cookies(makes 140 cookies)
directions: Milk can be soured by adding 1 teaspoon lemon juice or vinegar.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Roll out on floured board and cut in any shape you want.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade, milk and food coloring.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with lemon slices, mint leaves and whip cream.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, pineapple and walnuts. Add flour.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise.
Combine flour, cheese and salt.
Place in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time, coating with cheese mixture.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in layer in pan.
If any cheese is left, sprinkle over top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Turn once while baking. When golden brown, sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Debone and cut up chicken.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Take celery soup and chicken soup (I heat the soup until it is warm and mixed), pour the soups over chicken breasts.
Pour over the soup the chicken broth
plus sweet milk.
Mix flour and butter.
Mix this until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour or until brown.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Blend together.
Pour slowly into browned bacon.
Serve over endive or dandelion.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Cook to lukewarm.

title: lamb shanks en daube
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Saute onion and carrot until limp. Push to sides of pan.
Add shanks and brown on all sides.
Stir in stock, wine, salt, thyme, garlic and orange peel.
Cover and cook in 325° oven for 2 hours or until shanks are tender.
Remove to platter and keep warm.
Over direct heat, boil down pan juices until slightly reduced.
Skim fat.
Add tomatoes and spoon sauce over shanks.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix these ingredients together using dry Bisquick.
Form into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
These may be frozen before baking and placed in oven before thawing.

title: st. timothy coffee cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually; continue to cream.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and raisins; coat well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream; blend well.
The batter looks like whipped cream tinged with honey.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes, or until the cake tests done. Leave in pan for at least 1 hour before turning out.
Turn out; sprinkle with more cinnamon sugar.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine diced cucumbers, green pepper, pimiento and onion in a large bowl with parsley, basil and garlic.
Mix in Italian vinaigrette dressing.
If using canned tomatoes, strain the liquid from tomatoes and add it to the soup.
Coarsely chop tomatoes and add to soup along with tomato juice.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli with onion and cook as directed on broccoli package; drain.
Combine vegetables with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix next 5 ingredients until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: low-fat buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and Promise.
Beat and add egg whites.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.
Works best in a Bundt cake pan.
Serve with warm jelly, Cool Whip or fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter krisp
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter.
Stir until creamy. Pour mixture over the cereal.
Mix thoroughly until all cereal is well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and enjoy. Store in air tight container.
This freezes well.

title: *pecan crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut with pastry blender until mixture is blended.
Round up in 2 balls.
Roll very thin on cloth covered pastry board.
Brush each half with unbeaten egg white. Top with chopped pecans.
Cut into squares.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Place chicken in baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Mix other ingredients (except almonds). Pour over chicken and sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Use sauce as gravy over mashed potatoes.

title: hot crossed buns
directions: Mix in order listed.
Cover, let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls/buns, if desired brush with egg white.
Let rise again.
Cut crosses on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Pipe powdered sugar icing on crosses on top of buns.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook 3 hours at 325°, except green pepper.
Add 1 1/2 to 3 cups water after removing roast from liquids.
Put in green pepper (sliced).
Slice roast and put in liquid.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: dutch cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Sprinkle with salt, cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Rinse and drain cucumber.
Combine onion in bowl with sour cream, vinegar, dill seed and sugar.
Toss.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy frozen dessert
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Bake in a 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned; cool.
Beat remaining ingredients with electric mixer until blended.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cover dish and refreeze.
Lemonade concentrate may be substituted.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: chicken palermo
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Flatten breasts with the edge of a knife or pound slightly.
Place one slice of cheese on each chicken piece and roll cheese inside. Roll each chicken piece in butter, then in bread crumbs.
Place in the baking dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with sauce and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: onion cheese corn bread
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and saute.
Pour off melted butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Empty muffin mix into bowl.
Blend in egg, milk and corn.
Spread in baking pan.
Top with onion, sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Very good warm.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Blend all ingredients with a spoon.
Put in the freezer for 15 minutes to set.
Then store in the refrigerator.

title: baked fish a la mil
directions: Put fish fillets in baking pan.
Saute onion, pepper, garlic and tomatoes with olive oil.
Add basil, parsley, vinegar, soy sauce, wine and bread crumbs to onion and pepper mixture.
Season to taste.
Spoon mixture on each fish fillet.
Bake at 375° until fish is opaque and flakes easily.
Top fillets with Feta cheese. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: nacho cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing well.
Slowly add milk, stirring mixture constantly, until a velvety white sauce forms.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.
Slice cheese into small chunks for easy melting and stir into white sauce.
Stir until all cheese is melted.
Spoon over nacho chips.

title: grandma's slow cooker vegetarian chili
directions: In a slow cooker, combine black bean soup, kidney beans, garbanzo beans, baked beans, tomatoes, corn, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Season with garlic, chili powder, parsley, oregano and basil.
Cook for at least two hours on high.
This is a simple crowd pleasing recipe that can sit in a slow cooker until it is time to serve.
Prep time:
approx. 10 minutes.
Cook time: approx. 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Mash with milk.
Mix remaining ingredients, reserving 1/4 of cheese for garnish.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (last 20 minutes, uncover until golden brown).

title: pizza snacks
directions: Flatten biscuits and spread into 4 to 5 inch circles.
Brown ground beef or sausage with onion.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce and any other toppings such as green pepper, etc.
Pour on biscuits.
Top with cheese and bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Chop up vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in tortillas.
Slice and serve with picante.

title: make ahead baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onions in grease.
Stir in barbecue sauce, sugar and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Beans may be added at this point or sauce may be refrigerated or frozen and beans added when needed.

title: oatmeal apricot bars
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Press 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apricot jam (or any other you may prefer) over oatmeal mixture.
Top with remaining mixture, pressing lightly on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: satay
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
This makes an excellent marinade for any kind of meat, whether it's game or domestic. Marinate meat 4 hours or longer and then barbecue or stir-fry the meat.

title: fun fudge
directions: Can substitute any flavor chips.

title: mrs. harris' pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and milk.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Spread crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit-glaze pie
directions: Slice fruit into baked pie shells.
Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch in medium saucepan. Add cold water and lemon juice. Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Spoon hot glaze over fruit in pie shells.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor.
Add sugar and drained pineapples.
Let stand overnite.
When ready to serve, fold bananas, nuts, marshmallows and cranberries into the Cool Whip.

title: spinach chicken
directions: Dip each breast portion as follows:
First, in milk, second, in flour, third, in beaten eggs and fourth in Italian bread crumbs.
In skillet, melt butter and add minced garlic.
Brown breaded breasts well.
Remove and place in casserole dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Stir until it begins to thicken. Add sour cream and Cool Whip; beat until smooth.
In a very, very large dish, place layer of cakes and sliced bananas.
Cover with mixture. Continue until you have 3 layers. Cover top with mixture. Set in refrigerator and keep cold. This make a real large pudding.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, lemon juice, fruit juice and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve over fruit.

title: wassail(dry mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in airtight container.
To use, put 2 tablespoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: zesty broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into pieces.
Add onion, mayo, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Cook the bacon strips until brown and crispy, then crumble into mix.
Let sit overnight.
Just before serving, mix in 2 cups of cheese and egg.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat pie roma
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and cook until tender. Stir in sauce mix, tomato paste and water.

Simmer 10 minutes. Line greased 9-inch pie plate with biscuits, press together. Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over crust; fill with half of meat mixture, 2 slices Mozzarella cheese, remaining meat mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut remaining Mozzarella cheese slices into lengthwise strips. Arrange on pie in lattice pattern; return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown chopped onion and hamburger meat together.
Put in large dish and add rest of ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranapple wine
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and chill 8 hours.
Strain and discard cinnamon and cloves.
Combine syrup mixture, Burgundy and cranapple juice. Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: barbecued pork ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
This cuts out a lot of the fat so the ribs are healthier for you and less fattening.
Drain ribs and arrange in a shallow baking pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over ribs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn ribs over and bake another 30 minutes.

title: al's cabbage salad dressing
directions: Mix and serve over cabbage.

title: golden turkey quiche
directions: Bake pie shell
at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cook celery for 10 minutes or
until tender.
Stir in turkey and pimento.
Beat together eggs,
milk,
mayonnaise,
salt
and mustard.
Stir in turkey mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at
for
25 to 35 minutes.
Inserted knife should come out clean when done.

title: osgood pie
directions: Beat yolks lightly, add sugar, butter, vinegar and spices. Beat the whites until stiff and mix into mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake filling and crust at one time.

title: gravad lax appetizers
directions: In cup, combine salt, sugar and peppercorns.
Rub into all sides of fish.
Sprinkle with brandy.
Place 1/3 of dill in shallow glass baking dish.
Put 1 piece of fish skin side down on dill. Top with another 1/3 of dill.
Add another piece of fish skin side up and top with remaining dill.
Cover salmon with plastic wrap. Set plate larger than salmon on it.
Place 2 heavy cans of food on top.
Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup and vegetables. Set aside; then mix together flour, butter and milk. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic chicken(serves 8)
directions: Use boneless, skinless chicken breasts and cut into 1 x 2-inch cubes. Cover well with garlic salt; put in container dish and cover with buttermilk. Stir until well coated; cover with lid and let it marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: Cook chicken.
In skillet in hot margarine, cook garlic 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese. Heat to boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yogurt coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in yogurt and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.

title: greek style macaroni bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients. Set aside.
Combine next 2 ingredients.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick (do not boil).
Beat next 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in sauce.
Add macaroni. Spoon half of macaroni mixture into 2-quart oblong baking dish. Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: primavera salad
directions: Cook tortellini, drain and rinse.
Drain well.
Mix tortellini, pepper, broccoli, carrot and olives.
In a separate bowl mix pesto, milk and pepper.
Combine sauce with tortellini combination.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Punch holes in cake.
Prepare jello as directed; pour over cake.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese and Cool Whip together; spread on cake.
Place thawed strawberries on top.

title: mac sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cook sausage in water 15 minutes.
Mix macaroni, cheese and tomatoes in casserole.
Top with sausage links.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Cook 4 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: mom's anise bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside.
Scald milk and water combination (3 cups), adding sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool. Add molasses and yeast mix.
Mix the flours and add, kneading and keeping dough a bit softer than for white bread.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down twice. Shape into loaves and let rise a little before baking at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add warm water, lemonade, peach nectar and pineapple juice.
Stir well.
Add cold water. Freeze in 4 equal size containers.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 40 servings.

title: coconut chews
directions: Press and flatten with hand to cover a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt, pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and water; beat well.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place tomatoes on sheet in single layer.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn once.

title: goose soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter over medium heat until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Slowly add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer until slightly thickened.
Add cream and heat slowly until warm.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given.
Do not stir. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Make layers.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: lucille's pecan pie(4 small or 3 large pies)
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut Crisco in well.
Add just enough ice water to make dough hold together when stirred with a fork.
Roll out on waxed paper and transfer into a Pyrex pie plate.

title: pig in the blanket
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast softened in lukewarm water.
Add egg.
Gradually stir in flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down, break off pieces of dough, flatten out to roll around wieners.
Place in greased oblong pan.
Cover and let rise again. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: strawberry or coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake as directed.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out fairly clean.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together; add egg-milk mixture, beating as you pour.
Continue beating until smooth.
Let batter stand a few minutes while you heat 3 to 4 inches of fat to 375°.
Pour batter into small pitcher for easier handling.
Take an ordinary household funnel and put your finger over the end of it.
Pour some batter into mouth of funnel; take off your finger and let batter drop into hot fat, swirling it around and around until it is 3 inches in diameter.
Fry until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot. Makes about 12 cakes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl with wooden spoon. Stir in remaining ingredients; pour in pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: methodist munchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease several baking sheets.
Mix sugars, margarine and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 16 dozen cookies.
Delicious.

title: acorn squash a la stacey
directions: Scoop pulp and seeds out of the squash halves.
Place in deep baking dish, hallow side up.
Put 1 tablespoon butter in each half.
Fill hollow with syrup, covering cut surface of squash. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, nuts, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, cocoa, egg yolks, evaporated milk and a pinch of salt, if desired.
Add milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat until thick and smooth.
Add vanilla.
Put in baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix sauce and pour it over the chicken legs in a casserole dish (single layer).
Cook, uncovered, at 400° for about 1 hour. (Time varies with size of drumsticks.)
Turn the drumsticks once during the middle of the cooking time.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Steam broccoli until crisp-tender. Arrange in lightly greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with ham, green pepper, onion and cheese. In a blender or food processor, combine milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper. Blend until smooth. Pour over broccoli mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until set and lightly browned. Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle crunch
directions: Mix together all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and cover with Crunch Topping below.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves and cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water and spins a thread.
Pour over egg whites that have been beaten until thick.
Add nuts and flavoring and beat until it loses its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop artichoke hearts and combine with other ingredients.
Use 1 jar of the juice from the marinated artichokes.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool to room temperature and cut into squares.

title: beef-macaroni-chili skillet
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; pour off drippings.
Add macaroni, onion, salt, chili powder, sugar and pepper.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Combine tomato paste and the 1/4 cup of water.
Add to meat mixture and continue cooking 10 minutes.
(May add a quart of home canned tomatoes.)

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Stir in corn, potatoes, water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add milk and half and half.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated. Yields 8 cups.

title: cheery cherry loaf(my christmas bread)
directions: Drain red cherries, reserving liquid.
Add water if needed to equal 1/3 cup.
Cut up cherries; set cherries and liquid aside.

title: best potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Drain and beat with mixer.
Add all ingredients, except for Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Spray layer casserole dish with Pam or butter.	Pour potatoes in dish.	Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits; return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 12.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle cheese and 1/2 of the bacon into pastry shell.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over cheese and bacon. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with bacon halves and continue baking for 35 minutes or until firm and browned.
Cut into wedges.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread salsa over bottom layer.
Top with layers of shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, shredded cheese and sliced olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bachelorette beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in tightly covered Dutch oven. Bake in a 300° oven for 5 hours. Do not open oven at anytime. Do not increase amounts of any ingredients.

title: louise rulfo's pineapple icebox cake(very attractive!  an elegant dessert to make a day ahead)
directions: Combine drained pineapple syrup with 3/4 cup water and gelatin.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and sugar.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool.
Beat egg whites.
Then whip 1 pint of cream and fold egg whites and cream together.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and gelatin mixture.

Line 9-inch spring-form pan with split ladyfingers, standing them upright around sides. Trim tips which extend over top and use to fill spaces on bottom. Spoon in gelatin mixture and use remaining ladyfingers over top. Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours.
To serve, remove from pan and frost with remaining 1/2 pint whipping cream, flavored with sugar and sherry.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Note: Batter will be runny.)

title: carnation meat loaf
directions: Mix lightly and place in loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water; add 1/2 of flour, salt & sugar, beating with electric mixer or dough hook, add eggs, Crisco and remaining flour.
May have to stir some of flour in by hand, since it gets to stiff for mixer. Cover tightly & place in refrigerator to rise.
The dough will need to be punched down 2 or 3 times before it stops rising.
Two hours before serving time roll dough out to about 1/3 inch thickness, brush tops with melted butter or margarine.
Bake in 450° oven until golden brown.
I usually make these up the day before I plan to serve them so they will finish rising before bedtime.
I always buy yeast with the furtherest expiration date away.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cook the raisins and drain.

title: corn clam chowder
directions: Mix and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Bake in a roaster for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Take skin off chicken legs.
Boil in 6 cups of water until done.
Take chicken off the bone; discard the bones.
Pour vegetables in pot with chicken.
Pour tomatoes in pot.
Season to taste.
Add parsley.
Boil slowly for twenty minutes.
Enjoy with saltines or your favorite sandwich.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together, except bacon (lay on top).
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well in saucepan.
Add egg yolk; blend well.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Blend in butter and vanilla.
Cover and cool to lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Pour into pie crust, top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: cracker-n-vegetable lasagna
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook and stir red pepper, onion, zucchini and oregano in margarine until tender.
In lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half each of the crackers, vegetables and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Melt together the sugar and butter over low heat.
Let cool enough not to cook eggs.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add nuts.
Add dry mixture to butter and sugar. Add vanilla. Beat.
Grease pan with butter.
Pour mixture into greased pan and cook 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cook in oblong pan like used for layer cake.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix everything together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups corn flakes with melted butter.
Spread evenly on top of mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can be prepared and frozen for later use.

title: chicken breasts delight
directions: Wrap each
breast
with a bacon strip.
Cover bottom of baking dish
(greased),
x
12 x 2-inch, with chipped beef. Place chicken on top of chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and cover chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated.

title: raspberry chip cookies
directions: *Can substitute 1 teaspoon vanilla extract with 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.

title: all bran brown bread
directions: Mix together the All-Bran, sour milk and raisins and let sit a few minutes.
Sift together the sugar, flour and baking soda.
Add molasses and the flour mixture to the All-Bran mixture.
Fill greased and floured coffee can about 2/3 full and steam for three hours.
Place can on rack in large pan.
Fill with water halfway up can.
Cover and start timing when water boils.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pan; stir until boils.
Cover 1 minute.
Uncover; turn down to medium and cook until forms soft ball in water.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Leave awhile and let cool.
Whip until it loses its gloss.
Pour into greased pan.

title: grandpa's chili
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Add garlic salt, chili powder and Accent.
Simmer all ingredients 45 minutes.

title: fudgy applesauce cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until creamy; beat in eggs. Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Add dry ingredients to creamy mixture with the applesauce and the milk. Stir until blended.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato-onion country ribs
directions: Dredge	ribs
in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown ribs in an electric skillet.
Top with onion slices, potato slices and mushrooms.	Dilute	soup
with mushroom juice and enough water to make
soup can full.
Pour over ribs.	Reduce heat to simmer. Add
salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until ribs are tender and vegetables are done.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven.
Add water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Bone chicken, and cut meat into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Bring broth to a boil; add pepper.

title: world famous garlic bread(low-fat)
directions: In a small double boiler, melt the margarine.
Peel the garlic and using a garlic press, press the garlic into a small bowl.
Mix well with the mayonnaise and melted margarine and salt.

title: peach nut cake
directions: Mix all together, beating well.
Pour batter in three 8 x 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: lillian's salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil; add Sweet 'N Low and Jell-O.
Stir well to dissolve.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Congeal.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp well.
Pat dry and spread in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except bread in medium saucepan and let simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture over shrimp and mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, stirring through every 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake shrimp, turning frequently, until they just turn pink, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Serve in soup bowls with chunks of French bread to soak up the sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: amish tea
directions: Simmer for 45 minutes on low heat.
Do not boil!
Strain. Serve hot.
May be refrigerated up to 2 weeks.

title: ukrainian supper(borscht; very good)
directions: In a heavy pot put 10 cups cold water, soup meat, soup bones and pig knuckles.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add leek or onion, carrot and parsley.
Reduce heat and let simmer uncovered 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add more liquid when needed.
Cool, then refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Discard surface fat.
Strain stock; set aside meat and bones.
Return liquid to pot, adding water if necessary to make 8 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes, cabbage, tomato puree and garlic.
Simmer covered 30 minutes.
Add beets. Bring again to a boil.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Wash and core apples, but do not pare.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients in large skillet; simmer 5 minutes.
Place apples in syrup; cook for 5 minutes, turning carefully.
Transfer rings to shallow bowl. Strain syrup over apples.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Serve chilled as a meat garnish.
Makes about 24 rings.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Place oleo, chocolate chips and eggs in top of a double boiler.
Cook until chocolate chips are melted.
Set aside until cooled.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar and eggs with margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy baked carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese. Bake in baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: big bucket in the sky
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in dry ingredients, then lay chicken in pan of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or deep fry in oil.

title: cherry sherry sauce for ham
directions: Drain juice from cherries into saucepan.
Add juice from oranges and lemon, then add ginger, brown sugar and sherry. Place on low heat and stir occasionally to make sure sugar is dissolved.
As ham bakes, spoon a couple of tablespoons of sauce over it at various intervals.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together egg, sugar and shortening.
Add in molasses and milk.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Roll very thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400°.

title: judith's pecan pound cake
directions: Mix oil, milk, margarine, vanilla, baking powder, sugar and flour. Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat well. Add chopped pecans, rolled in flour. Stir in with a spoon. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: kibbie in kesck
directions: In a kettle, fry the meat, garlic and onions (allee).
Then add the cabbage.
Cook until cabbage wilts.
Then you add your Kesck, stir it, but not hard.
Add water, about 1/2 kettle full. Keep stirring until it boils.
Then lower the fire and let it simmer.
Drop the Kibbie balls into the broth.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls.
Serves 4 people.

title: frozen chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with coffee in top of double boiler over hot water.
While mixture is hot, whisk in the eggs, rum and vanilla until smooth.
Cool 5 minutes.
Whip 1 cup cream until stiff. Gently fold into chocolate mixture.
Blend completely.
Pour into crust and freeze about 1 hour before serving.
Transfer to refrigerator.
Whip remaining 1/2 cup cream and dollop over pie. Sprinkle with chocolate shavings.
Pie can be frozen up to 3 months.
Can use plain or chocolate graham crust.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil and boil one minute the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
These can be peanut butter instead of chocolate just by leaving out the cocoa.

title: kings hawaiian dip
directions: Mix all together; let set overnight.
Serve with Hawaiian bread and raw vegetables.

title: cherry choco bars
directions: Beat eggs by hand.
Add cake mix, pie filling and vanilla. Stir until mixed; do not beat.
Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine dry ingredients, milk and melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Top with pecans and drizzle with honey. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender. Serves 6.

title: italian meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together egg whites, garlic, basil, salt, rosemary and red pepper.
Then stir in onions and bread crumbs.
Add turkey and mix until well combined.
Spray a loaf pan with no-stick spray.
Pat turkey mixture in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Spread spaghetti sauce over the top of the turkey.
Bake 25 minutes more or until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over the top.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake until done. Melt caramels with milk in double boiler.
Pour over cake.
Add chips and pecans.
Pour in rest of cake mix and bake until done.

title: fried rice
directions: Preheat oil in wok at 375°.
Stir-fry rice, garlic and ginger root until rice is slightly crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add scallions and shrimp; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce and pepper; stir.
Push rice mixture up the sides of the wok.
Stir to break up eggs as they cook.
When eggs have cooked, stir together with rice.
Serve immediately.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs; add flavors to make a paste with cocoa and food coloring.
Mix well.
Alternatively add flour (with salt) and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl, then add to batter.
Blend well.
Pour in three 9-inch or 10-inch pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When toothpick comes clean from cake it's done but don't overcook.
Let cool completely.
Ice with butter frosting or French vanilla!
Yum! Yum!

title: golden turkey lasagna
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in melted oleo.
Stir in mushrooms, pimento, soup, milk and basil.
Heat.
Arrange 1/2 of noodles in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Layer 1/2 sauce, cottage cheese, turkey and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Soak the cucumbers in the water and pickling salt overnight. Drain well; combine with the onion, red and green peppers and celery.
Heat the remaining ingredients; boil hard for 3 minutes. Add the rest; simmer for 10 minutes.
Put in hot jars to seal. Let set for at least 1 week.

title: easy egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and boiling water.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
(I use nutmeg only.)
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: linguine salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook corn.
Mix with cracker crumbs, milk, butter and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cut green pepper in small pieces.
Saute in a small amount of butter and add to mixture.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and season with salt and pepper.
Place bacon over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen mixed vegetables for 2 minutes, then drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, onion, grated cheese and chopped celery.
Mix with vegetables and put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheese vegetable chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add cabbage, onions, celery and carrots.
Cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add corn, peas, milk, thyme and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Heat gently, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Salt to taste.

title: bean and guacamole dip
directions: Layer in a 9-inch pie dish starting with beans.
Serve with large Fritos for a dip.

title: fig-strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients well; let set for 30 minutes.
Simmer for 5 minutes, cooking slowly.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: cake face
directions: Eggs go in first.
Then take them out so it can make a face cake.
Put the face on it.

title: spicy dilled beans
directions: One or two days before serving:
In large stainless steel-lined saucepan, mix vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper over medium heat.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Pour into 2-quart, shallow glass baking dish; cool completely.

title: mom's nut bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and melt cheese.
Pour the cheese and ground beef together, put on warm and set aside.
Put chips on a plate, pile on cheese and ground beef mixture.
Put on the taco sauce and sour cream and enjoy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease and flour or
spray
pizza
pan with Pam.
Slice cookies and cover pan
with slices.
Bake according to package directions; cool.
Mix preserves with 2 or 3 tablespoons water and heat; cool.
Mix
cream
cheese,
sugar
and vanilla until creamy. Spread on cookie
crust.
Arrange fruit in any design you like. With pastry
brush,
spread
cooled
preserves over fruit.
Place in refrigerator (covered).

title: easy stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven and bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: aunt marsha's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans; pat loosely in 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with mixer. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip. Beat with mixer the pudding with milk. Place in refrigerator until ready to use. Spread Cool Whip/cream cheese mixture over cooled crust. Spread pudding over Cool Whip/cream cheese. Cool 20 minutes in refrigerator.
Then add remainder of Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate sprinkles. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: rice and veggies
directions: Saute vegetables in a pan.
Cook rice.
Once rice is cooked, stir rice into the pan of vegetables.
Season to taste and serve.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix.
(If like thinner chili, add water.)
Cover and simmer on low until heated thoroughly.
Serve with rice or crackers.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into approximately 1 1/2-quart of broth.
Cook 5 minutes without lid and then 10 minutes with lid.

title: lemon bavarian
directions: Mix Jell-O and water and cool in refrigerator until almost set up.
Add whipped cream and chilled lemon pie filling.
Beat together and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in tube pan (preferably a large one) for 1 hour at 325°.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a saucepan and bring to a boil over moderate heat, then remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and pour in Rice Krispies.
Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat in separate pan.
Butter a square pan and put in the mixture.
Pour melted butterscotch morsels over mixture.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Chop partially thawed broccoli. In saucepan, combine soup, milk and butter.
Mix together until blended.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, broccoli, celery and onion.
Place ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, flour and syrup all together, then add flavor and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done at 325°.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Add boiling water to orange juice to make 1 cup.
Combine rind and dates in a mixing bowl.
Stir in soda, sugar and shortening. Add egg; sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to wet mixture.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cranberry chicken
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces and brown in margarine.
Remove chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cranberry sauce, in skillet with drippings.
Heat on low for 5 minutes.
Place chicken in a large casserole dish.
Pour liquid mixture over and around chicken.
Add cranberry sauce on top.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Arrange peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until browned.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in molasses, salt, shortening, caraway seed and rye flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough white flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Cover; let rest 10 to 15 minutes. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough; round up, cover and let rise again until double, about 40 minutes.
Grease a baking sheet; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Punch down dough; divide in half.
Shape each half into round, slightly flat loaf.
Place loaves in opposite corners of baking sheet.
Cover; let rise 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs and butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and dab with butter.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, until bread crumbs are crusty.

title: linda's squash casserole
directions: Boil the squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain well; add 1 stick of margarine, the cheeses, and the soup; mix well. Pour into greased casserole. Mix together the crackers with melted margarine; pour on top of the squash mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Allow pudding to stand 5 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip into pudding.
Pour half of this mixture over graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers. Top this with other half of pudding mixture.
End with third layer of graham crackers.
Spread the top with can of chocolate frosting or use your favorite chocolate icing.
Allow the dessert to stand in the refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Can stand 48 hours.

title: mexi-melts
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain grease.
Stir in salsa and let simmer.
Melt cheeses together.
Microwave the tortillas 2 minutes.
Fill tortillas with meat; pour cheese on meat.
Heat Mexi-melts in microwave for 1 minute just before serving.
Dip in salsa, sour cream, etc.

title: cherry cheese dream pie
directions: Slice 1 to 2 bananas on cooled pie crusts.
Mix softened cream cheese and sugar together, then fold in not quite 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Put this mixture over the sliced bananas. Top with 1/2 can cherry pie filling. Freeze at least 2 hours. Take out about 15 minutes before serving and cut.
You may refreeze the rest.
Pies will stay about 4 days before the bananas turn dark.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix melted margarine and egg together.
Add both cans of corn. Add sour cream and Jiffy corn muffin mix.
Mix well and bake at 350°.

title: aunt jenny's chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise together.
Layer in a casserole dish the chicken, water chestnuts and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° about an hour or until middle bubbles.
Sprinkle top with onion rings and cook 5 minutes more.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Set until jells in refrigerator. Drain can of pineapple and save juice. Add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas to jello. Place in 8 x 10 glass or sheet cake pan. In saucepan combine 1/2 cup pineapple juice, butter, egg, flour and sugar. Cook over low heat until thickened. Add cream cheese to warm mixture and stir until dissolved. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box and add to cooled topping. Spread topping over jello mixture and refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares. Serves 12 to 16.

title: cauliflower ring
directions: Cook margarine, flour and milk until thick; add mayonnaise. Combine with remaining ingredients. Turn into well-greased 1 quart ring mold or casserole. Set in shallow pan of hot water. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm. Unmold on heated platter and fill center of mold with English peas or green beans.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together; pour into baking dish and bake in 300° oven 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to chicken mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shrimp saladgroves, texas
directions: Boil peeled and clean shrimp in seasoned water.
Add 1/2 of onion to water and cool.

title: mini-pizza
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Add onion; cook until onion is soft. Mix in paste, sauce and seasoning.
Spread on muffin.
Top with cheese and green onion.
Place on baking sheet; broil 2 to 4 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugar with sherry and boil until it will form a soft ball in cool water.
Add cinnamon and nuts, stirring until cloudy. Turn mixture onto a well buttered cookie sheet, separating nuts; cool.
May be stored in covered jars.

title: pat's pizza dough
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, salt, sugar, yeast and water in bowl. Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Let rise 10 minutes. Cook 10 minutes, then add your toppings.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix 1 box of jello with 2/3 cup of boiling water.
Cool; add 2/3 cup of milk.
Let set in a 9 x 13-inch pan in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together; freeze.
Can be put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, milk, chopped onion, green chopped pepper and eggs into the hamburger and mix together.
Put in a baking pan and put into oven at 350° for from 1 to 2 hours until done.

title: larry's beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Fry beef in skillet.
Add beef to noodles.
Add remaining ingredients except milk.
Stir.
Add milk and stir.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves six.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole dish (9 x 13-inch), layer chicken, then broccoli. Mix mayonnaise and soups.
Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with cheese, then Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and chopped nuts.
Add cocoa, syrup and rum; mix well.
Coat hands with confectioners sugar and roll mixture into balls 1/2 to 3/4-inch in diameter.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Roll in confectioners sugar and serve.

title: texas grits casserole
directions: Bring the water to a boil and add grits and the salt.
Let simmer for 6 minutes.
Saute the green peppers and onions in the butter.
Add to the cooked grits, the onion-pepper-butter mixture, cheese, chili powder, eggs and milk.
Pour into a 1 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm. Sprinkle with cheese at the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: chicken in dutch oven(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Mix together in Dutch oven all cans of soup (do not add liquid) and rice.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture; sprinkle with dried onion soup.
Cover; place into the coals to cook for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: henry's favorite cream hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add a scant tablespoon of butter or margarine.
Mix ingredients and cook well.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Blend the flour, margarine and powdered sugar with a pastry blender until it resembles corn meal.
Pat into 8-inch square ungreased cake pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Have steak cut 1 1/2-inch thick.
Pound flour into both sides of steak.
Heat fat in a frying pan.
Add and brown meat and onions in hot fat.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Add rest of ingredients, cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours until very tender.
Turn frequently to allow even cooking.

title: mother's sunshine bread or muffins
directions: Combine eggs, oil and milk in large bowl.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 2 well greased loaf pans for 60 minutes; 4 (1 pound) vegetable or fruit cans for 45 to 50 minutes or 24 muffins for 20 minutes.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and cinnamon until well blended; stir in apples.
Pour the mixture into pie shell; dot with 1 Tbsp butter or margarine.
Bake for 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and peppers; combine with cucumbers.
Add salt to vegetables; let set 3 hours. Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil. Pack in jars.
Process in boiling water bath.

title: lollipops
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Cook to exactly 300°.
Remove from heat; add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon and flavoring of your choice and 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon coloring of your choice.
Pour into greased lollipop molds.
When hard, remove from molds and put in bags.

title: sugar-free jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix other ingredients together. Pour into jello.
Chill.
This is very good for diabetics.

title: butter for corn-on-the-cob
directions: Mix together and use on hot corn-on-the-cob.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: good peanut butter crisscrosses
