directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla, eggs and peanut butter together with mixer and low speed. Add dry ingredients and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sand tarts (ladyfingers)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add 1 cup of flour with mixer, mixing well.
Add remaining flour, mixing with hand.
Add nuts.
Roll in finger shapes, crescents or balls.
Careful not to roll ends too thin.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, depending on size, in 300° oven.
You do not brown these.
When bottoms and edges start to brown, they should be done.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken over spinach
directions: Layer casserole dish with spinach (if frozen, just defrost in microwave and break up into pieces) or can use asparagus or broccoli.

title: butterscotch bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pecans and brown sugar. Grease and flour a bundt pan.
Pour half of the cake batter into the bundt pan.
Combine the pecans and brown sugar and sprinkle half of this mixture on the cake batter in the pan.
Pour the remaining cake batter into the pan.
Sprinkle with the remainder of the nut mixture.
Knife through the cake to distribute the nut mixture. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Let cool.
Remove cake from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and oil; batter will be stiff.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoonful into hands and roll into small balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with vanilla frosting or place 2 together to resemble an Oreo cookie.

title: banana raisin nut loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup bananas, shortening and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining bananas and vanilla.
Beat 1minute; fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted near middle.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together in bowl and roll into logs.
Cook at 250 for 2 hours.

title: pork chops with filling
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and place in shallow baking dish.
Lightly mix bread cubes, onion, butter and 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of filling on each pork chop. Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over pork chops and filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Shape ground beef into balls.
Cook over medium heat until brown all over.
Remove from pan.
Drain all but 5 tablespoons of grease from pan.
Add flour.
Stir until it is dark brown.
Add water, stirring it in slowly until desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper, then add meatballs to gravy and let simmer a few minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread or pat dough in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Spread over with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut, walnuts and chocolate candies.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Roll in small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Push a thumb print into each one and add cherry pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: In iron skillet, cook sausage, stir with wooden spoon only, melt together all of cheese.
After creamy, add all Bisquick, quickly remove from fire.
Make small balls and pat down.
Bake in oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Spread strips sparingly with anchovy paste.
Wrap around oysters and secure with toothpicks, broil until done.
Yield 3 dozen.

title: moist fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder and add alternately with flavorings to creamed mixture.
Sprinkle remaining flour over nuts and fruits; add to batter.
Place brown paper in bottom of a tube pan and grease bottom and sides.
Place broiler pan containing water under cake pan in oven.
Bake 2 hours and 30 minutes at 250°.
When done boil syrup; pour over cake while hot.
Let stand all night in pan.
When removed from pan, wrap in cloth and foil; store in refrigerator.
Cake may be served immediately.
Yields 20 to 25 servings.

title: orange pie
directions: Take 3/4 cup sugar and add flour or cornstarch.
Place in kettle over fire and add hot water and butter.
Boil until thick. Take remainder of sugar, add yolks of 2 eggs, juice and rind of orange and stir into other mixture; cook until thick (may also add small amount of lemon juice, rind or flavoring).
Pour into pastry and top with meringue made from the whites of eggs used for filling.

title: easy baked cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, salt, flour, orange peel, lemon peel and 2 of the eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Continue beating, adding remaining eggs and egg yolk, 1 at a time.
Beat in 1/4 cup whipping cream on low speed.
Pour into crusts.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 200° and bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven; leave cheesecake in oven 15 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours but no longer than 48 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; add cranberry sauce and cool until set.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in mold.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips and condensed milk.
Add vanilla and salt; mix.
Add marshmallows; melt completely.
Pour into a buttered pan and refrigerate to set.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Measure the brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt into saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over freshly popped corn and peanuts.
Mix well and turn out on cookie sheets or cake pans.
Place in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally while in oven.
When corn is removed from oven and cooled enough to handle, the kernels can easily be separated and stored in tightly covered containers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift dry ingredients two or three times and add nuts and dry ingredients. Blend thoroughly with other mixture; add carrots, a small amount at a time, and blend well.
Makes 3 layers.
Cook at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes for layers, 1 hour for loaf or tube pan.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves to a boil. Remove from heat and add tea bags. Let stand for 15 minutes. Remove tea bags. Add orange juice and lemon juice. Strain. Serve hot. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first four ingredients, stir in pecan halves. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery, then drain. Separately heat soup and milk, then pour over meat mixture.
Add Tater Tots.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: finest cherry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with pastry.
Sprinkle with one tablespoon flour and one tablespoon sugar.
Drain cherries, saving juice. Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in cherry juice. Add almond extract and lemon juice.
Combine with cherries and pour into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust in place.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 425° oven.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Wash firm tomatoes and slice the way you like them.
Place on cookie sheets and put in freezer until frozen.
Take out and place in Ziploc freezer bags.
To fry take out ever how many you want to fry and dip in meal.
Fry in shortening of your choice.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: beef brisket in wine
directions: Place meat in roasting pan with 4 cups of water, wine, and Gravy Master.
Top meat with onion, soup and sliced onion.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Remove and add wild rice. Return to oven and cook 1 hour longer or until most of gravy is absorbed.
Mound rice around meat.

title: cherry cranberry pie
directions: Combine cranberries, brown sugar and spices in 2-quart saucepan.
Add 1/3 cup reserved cherry juice (adding water if necessary to make 1/3 cup).
Cover and cook over medium heat until approximately 2/3 of cranberries have popped, about 15 minutes. Blend cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water until smooth.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Add cherries and cook until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and almond extract.
Let cool.
Fit first crust into pie pan.
Turn filling into crust.
Dot with butter pieces.
Brush egg and water mixture onto second crust and cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Arrange strips in lattice pattern on top of pie.
Flute edges.
Bake 25 minutes to 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Mix and make into burger patties.
When burgers are done, put a slice of Mozzarella cheese on top and let melt.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the bottom of the pan, put in coconut and nuts.
Add on top of that the German chocolate cake mix (mixed up).
Melt butter and mix together with cream cheese and confectioner sugar.
Spread on top of cake.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli carrot stir-fry
directions: Peel stems off broccoli.
Cut off 1 1/2-inch flowerets. Thinly slice stems.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil.
Add broccoli, carrots and ginger.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add water and soy sauce.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and mustard in a large mixing bowl.
Add potatoes, seasonings, onion, celery and 4 eggs. Toss lightly until well mixed.
Spoon the mixture into serving bowls and garnish with remaining eggs.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: smoky cheese spread
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Add liquid smoke and blend thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour and confectioners sugar until it is like pie dough.
Press into a 7 x 11-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While crust is baking, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour into baked crust and continue to bake until brown.

title: enchilada casserole(yummy)
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic powder and onion.
Drain grease.
Add both cans tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam spray or grease lightly. Line bottom of pan with 6 tortillas.
Spread meat mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle half of cheese over meat.
Layer with 6 tortillas.
Mix soup and milk in bowl.
Pour over top tortillas. Spread over top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Can serve with lettuce, hot sauce, sour cream, etc.

title: fish patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in skillet 5 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: In large bowl, mix mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Sift, then resift flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to liquids in bowl and stir gently until batter is smooth.
Do not use mixer!
Pour in a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pan.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until done.
Frost when cool.

title: hattie's lemon cake
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to egg yolks, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice and cook over slow fire.
While hot, add Jell-O and 1/2 cup water; cool.
Beat cream and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into mixture.
Beat egg whites and add 1/4 cup sugar; fold into mixture.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups. Add to gelatin.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth. Fold in strawberries and chill until mixture will mound, about 15 minutes. Spoon into pie crust. Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with additional strawberries, if desired.

title: monkey pull apart
directions: Mix together 3/4 cup white sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits into quarters and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Drop into greased tube pan. Use remaining mixture and add 1/2 cup white sugar, brown sugar and butter. Bring this mixture to a boil. Pour over biscuits. Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove from pan immediately. Raisins and nuts may also be added before baking. Pull apart and enjoy.

title: great potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream of celery soup. Cover with water and boil until all ingredients are tender. Add soup. Serve with cornbread.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 7 to 8 hours. Stir occasionally.
Shred pork.

title: holiday pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl; stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: barley soup
directions: Combine broth, water and tomatoes in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook until boiling.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Lower heat, cover and cook for 10 minutes or until barley is tender.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender on high for one minute. Refrigerate.
Serve over ice.
Must stay refrigerated.

title: bun bars(candy)
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Spread 1/2 mixture on bottom of a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
(Chill.)
Combine butter, milk and pudding and boil for 1 minute.
Add powdered sugar; spread over chilled base.
Add peanuts to other half of chocolate mix.
Spread over top.
Cut into tiny squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: me mo's custard(serves 16)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Strain, then add mixture to gallon of milk.
Cook in double boiler.
Stir constantly until coats a silver spoon.
Won't get thick until cools.
Strain again when cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first three ingredients five minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes.
Set skins aside.
Bring pulp to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Press pulp through sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins to pulp.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add lemon juice, margarine and grape pulp.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, sugar and salt.
Mix well and add boiling water and margarine.
Cook until thick in a pan.
Remove the mixture from heat.
Add milk, eggs and baking powder and mix well. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from heat and set to cool 20 minutes before cutting.
Makes 24 servings.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Soak dried black-eyed peas in water overnight; drain. Place in a large kettle; cover with water. Add bay leaf, onion, bacon or ham hocks and red pepper pod. Cook until peas are tender. Add cooked rice, salt and pepper. Turn into a casserole; cover and bake at 350° until liquid is absorbed.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, sour cream and butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: simple fudge
directions: Mix everything, except butter and vanilla.
Cook until it forms soft ball in water.
Take off stove; add butter and vanilla. Pecans, if desired, can be added now.
Stir until cool.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut when cold.
Foolproof.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Blend in oil and water.
Add flour and cinnamon, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Beat in potatoes.
Mix well. Add raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 1 pound coffee can.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage pie
directions: Saute together sausage and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Bring syrup and brown sugar to a boil until sugar dissolves. Add Rice Krispies, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter and add flour; cook until smooth, then add onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add 1/2 cup reserved liquid.
Stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Stir in cheese until it melts.
Mix with spinach.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch uncovered, ungreased dish.
Cover with crushed crackers or bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain juice from salmon, reserving 1/4 c.
Dump salmon into a bowl and add egg and flour.
Mix until gummy.
Do not mix the following until ready to use.
Mix salmon juice and baking powder until it foams.
Combine foaming mixture with salmon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat.
Drain on paper towels.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash and mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese peas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chunked cream cheese.
Pour in English peas and stir until creamy.

title: copper pennies
directions: Let cool.
In container, combine carrots, onion, pepper, celery and sauce 24 hours before serving.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: shrimp crab salad
directions: Cut crust from bread and spread lightly with butter.
Cut into small cubes so each slice is at least 20 cubes.
Frozen bread cuts best.
Add onions and eggs.
Mix, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broken glass pie
directions: Dissolve each package of orange, lime and cherry jello in 1 cup hot water, then add 1/2 cup cool water. Chill.
Let these jello mixtures set firm before making next mixture.
Heat pineapple juice; dissolve lemon jello and sugar. Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Let set until syrupy, but not stiff. Whip the whipping cream; fold in jello-pineapple mixture (may use Dream Whip).
Cut up orange, lime and cherry jello into any shape and size and fold into whipped cream mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Nuts may be used if desired.

title: red pepper, country ham and cheese soup
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil and 1 tablespoon water in large saucepan.
Add fennel; cut into 1/8-inch strips the onion and celery.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, approximately 7 minutes.
Add red pepper and cook another 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Bring chicken broth to a boil in another saucepan.
Melt butter in separate saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and cook 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add the heated chicken broth and whisk until smooth.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add to the vegetables.
Then whisk in cheese little by little.
Add ham. Adjust seasonings and serve.
Can be made 1 day ahead.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add sugar, shortening, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fried taters*
directions: Peel and worsh* taters* , onyuns* and peppers.
Cut in little chunks or slice 'em.
Put in big arn* skillet that has a big hunk of lard melted in it and is hot.
Add taters* , onyuns* and peppers.
Fry til they git* brown.
Turn 'em ever so often til they git* done.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil. Allow to boil 15 minutes. Cool. Add juices. Place bananas in blender and liquify. Add to juices. Mix well. Freeze for at least 3 hours. (If frozen solid, remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.) Place in punch bowl and pour in ginger ale. Do not add ice. Serves 50.

title: tomato pie
directions: Press 1/2 of the biscuits into a 9-inch pie pan to form crust. Saute onion and pepper in oleo until tender.
Layer 1/2 onion and pepper in bottom of crust.
Put sliced tomatoes next, then remaining onion and pepper. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the mayonnaise and cheese together and spread on top.
Roll out remaining biscuits and fit on top as crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup of walnuts.
Form into two balls and roll into remaining walnuts (1 cup).
Also can be frozen!

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix well.
Shape into roll 2 1/2 inches in diameter. Roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
When ready to use, cut thin slices and place on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: pecan cheese dip
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and vinegar. Cook over boiling water until thick. Cool slightly. Beat in cheese. Add green pepper and onion. Add pecans.
Let stand for 2 hours.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Beat the 3 whole eggs with electric mixer; add the brown sugar and beat until well mixed.
Add the dry ingredients and milk; lastly stir in orange slices and nuts, floured with the tablespoon flour.
Bake in a pan, 10 x 13-inch, at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cut in pieces, 1 x 4-inch.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, soda, margarine and egg yolks together; mix until crumbly. Press into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Cook at 350° for 12-15 minutes. Place marshmallows on top and cook another 2-3 minutes until puffy.

title: easy rump roast
directions: Place roast in a Dutch oven; sprinkle with soup mix.
Pour in wine.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours, or until tender. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Prepare pastry for a 2-crust pie.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Mix together sugar, flour and nutmeg; add to egg mixture.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust. Bake in a 400° oven about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in long strips, then in 1-inch pieces.
Fry until brown.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over all and brown again.
Add mushrooms with liquid and 1 cup of water. Simmer until tender (at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Add sour cream and heat just before serving.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: garlic buttered green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water until tender.
In a skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add onion powder and garlic powder.

title: spinach dip
directions: Completely thaw and drain spinach; mix with soup mix, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Cut center out of bread; the top crust will fit like a lid after putting the dip inside the loaf.
Cut the removed bread into chunks to be spread with the dip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll medium thickness and cut out.
May be sprinkled with sugar or frosted.

title: sugar-n-spice cookies
directions: 1. Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg, molasses throughly. 2. Blend dry ingredients.
Stir into shortening mixture. Form in 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. 3. Bake 10-12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add green peppers and onion.
Mix in taco seasoning, sauce and paste, water and chili powder over medium heat.
Blend sour cream, eggs and pepper in small bowl.
Place 1/2 of tortillas on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 1/2 the meat mix.
Place 2 slices of cheese on top.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and noodle nests
directions: Cook ABC's al dente.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine ham, cheese, onions and ABC's.
Divide into muffin tins.
Beat eggs slightly; stir in cream, milk and salt.
Spoon liquid over noodle mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead, frozen and reheated.

title: dirty bird cake
directions: Blend well; do not beat.
Pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Remove the tough ends of stalks and cut flowerets and stems into small pieces.
Place in large bowl and add onions, celery, raisins and bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well. Add dressing to mixture and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Slice potatoes, peeled or unpeeled, in a casserole dish.
Place in layers the potatoes, meat and onions.
Pour soup over all and bake until potatoes are done, about 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven until it melts.
The garlic cheese may be used if this is desired.
Very quick and easy.
Serves about 4 people.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and milk until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from fire and add flavoring and nuts.
Beat as long as you can. Pour into buttered pan.

title: apple-kuchen cobbler bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch baking pan.

title: capusta (cooked cabbage)
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken with herbs en casserole
directions: Saute bacon in deep skillet until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Saute chicken pieces, a few at a time, in bacon fat until brown. When browned, place in 2 1/2-quart casserole, sprinkling crumbled bacon over each layer.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, celery salt, sage and thyme. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add to skillet.
Stir in milk. Stir over low heat until thickened and smooth.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovering the last 15 minutes.

title: instant rice pudding
directions: In 2-quart glass dish, mix together all ingredients.
Cook uncovered in microwave for 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Let rest for 15 minutes.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Do not substitute egg product.
Whole eggs must be used in this recipe.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil, debone and cut up chicken.
Retain 1 cup broth.
Combine soup and sauce with chicken.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch glass pan with Pam.
Line pan with Fritos.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Top with Fritos.
Pour broth over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer delight
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Break cake into bite size pieces.
Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Top with pie filling.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange torte
directions: Put flour, white sugar, salt and soda in large bowl and stir with spoon.
Then add eggs, vanilla and mandarin oranges with juice.
Mix well with mixer until oranges break up.
Bake in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: stir-fried scallops and vegetables
directions: Marinate scallops in lemon juice for 30 minutes.
In large skillet over high heat, cook and stir carrots and garlic in butter until tender-crisp, 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and thyme; cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch and salt into scallop mixture; add to vegetables.
Cook and stir until scallops are opaque, about 4 minutes.
Stir in onions, pea pods and sherry. Remove from heat.
Serve with rice.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice and stir until thick.
Add pitted cherries and nuts.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold other ingredients into whipped cream.
Pour into shell and chill until firm, about 21 hours.

title: mustard sauce for ham(use with ham loaf.)
directions: Blend melted butter with first 3 ingredients. Whip in 1 cup heavy cream or half and half.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1 egg yolk, mixing constantly until blended.
Add 1/4 cup warmed cider vinegar and allow to cool.
Serve at room temperature.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red chinese chicken
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and pour over poultry that has been placed in a Dutch oven.
Baste 2 to 3 times while baking. Bake at 350° covered for one hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, place steamed broccoli cut up in bite size pieces.
On top of broccoli, put chicken, also cut up in bite size pieces.
Over chicken, spread mixture of mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
On top, spread cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed franks
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Cut lengthwise slit in each frank. Spread open slightly and fill with stuffing.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: joudza(china)
directions: Make 24 circles.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, custard and 1 teaspoon of salt to pork.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in frying pan to 375°.
Add pork mixture and cook about 1 minute or until done.
Remove.
Set aside.
Cook leeks in 1 tablespoon of oil, about 1 minute, adding 1/4 teaspoon of salt. Remove.
Add to meat.
Using 2 tablespoons of oil and 1/4 teaspoon of salt, fry bamboo shoots.
Add meat mixture.
Cook 5 minutes. Drain and cool.
Mix 1 teaspoon of salt with flour.
Add hot water to tablespoon of flour at a time.
Add only enough water to form dough similar to pie crust.
Roll walnut-sized ball of dough on floured board to opaque 5-inch diameter circle.
Wrap about 2 tablespoons meat mixture in each circle, folding ends in sealing edges with flour and water paste.
Heat pint of oil to 375° in deep pan.
Fry golden brown.

title: oma's broken glass cake
directions: Dissolve each package of jello separately in 1 1/2 cups of hot water and let set overnight.
When ready to use, cut jello into chunks and mix all three colors together, that gives the effect of broken glass.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix and chill.
This can be used in molds or cut into squares and served on lettuce.

title: grape leaf pickles(kosher dills)
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Let stand in cold water overnight.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
To each quart add listed amount of alum, garlic, dill and hot pepper.
Combine vinegar, salt and water. Bring to a boil, fill jars and place grape leaf in each quart and seal.
(Can add onion.)

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal softies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix in uncooked oats.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Sift together flour; add flour alternately with milk. Blend.
Bake in a cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bubba gump's shrimp quickie
directions: Peel shrimp and leave tails on.
Combine dressing and remaining ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and stir well.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 25 minutes or until shrimp turns pink; stir occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: english muffin appetizer
directions: Blend well and spread on muffin halves.
Cut into small triangles.
Freeze and keep in plastic bag until ready to serve. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler for few minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, flour and orange peel.
Put half of fruit in a pie shell; sprinkle with half of orange peel mixture. Put remaining fruit in and sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Dot with butter.
Place on top pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 more minutes, or until juice bubbles.

title: aunt opal's crisp cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough for 1/2 hour.
Make into small balls (about the size of walnuts).
Dip in melted butter; roll in cinnamon sugar.
Flatten on cookie sheet, using the bottom of a drinking glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; pour over pineapple in greased glass baking dish.
Add cheese over the top; sprinkle cracker crumbs on the top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Goes well with ham dishes.

title: little reubens
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
Flatten and stretch out.
Put a small slice of corn beef, kraut, swiss cheese and dressing on roll.
Pull dough up around filling and seal completely.
Place on Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with graham cracker crust made with the crushed graham crackers and oleo.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 hours or until thick and a dark brown color. Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased layer pans.
Cool; frost with Sour Cream Chocolate Frosting.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Combine egg and milk in small bowl and mix well.
Pour into skillet.
Cook until set.
Cut into strips.
Saute onion tops, shrimp and garlic in oil in skillet.
Add rice and soy sauce. Cook until rice is heated through.
Stir in cooked egg.
Heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with additional onion tops.
Serves 4.

title: kluski potatoes(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until tender, cool and peel.
Cook Kluski egg noodle dumplings according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
Melt butter in a large heavy skillet.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in paprika and salt.
Put potatoes in skillet and break into large chunks with fork.
Add Kluski egg noodle dumplings and toss well to coat with butter and paprika mixture.
Heat through.

title: white rolls
directions: Place sugar, salt and shortening in a large bowl; add milk. Cool until lukewarm.
Put yeast in lukewarm water.
Add flour to make a batter too stiff to cling to bowl, but not stiff enough to knead.
Cover tightly and let rise in a warm room until double in bulk.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs until well mixed.
Beat flour mixture into eggs.
Beat in sugar, salt, syrup, butter and vanilla; add pecans.
Set oven to 325°.
Bake pie crust until it begins to cook (begins to puff, but is not completely done).
Pour in pecan filling.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(May be covered for the last 15 minutes baking time if needed to keep pecans from burning.)

title: angel pie
directions: Roll crackers very fine; set aside.
Beat egg whites until very stiff; add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add crackers, dates, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and place in greased pie pan and bake.
Cool in refrigerator and serve with vanilla ice cream and/or whipped topping or cut into small pieces and freeze.

title: chicken pedro
directions: Crush 1 bag of the Doritos. Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix together the chicken soup, chicken, sour cream, green chilies and onion. Pour this mixture over the crushed Doritos. Cover with the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly. Serve with salsa and Doritos.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with 6 cups boiling water and cook 1 hour.
Braise onions, green peppers and garlic in water.
Combine with beans; add other seasonings and cook until beans are tender and liquid is thick.
Serve over brown rice and sprinkle green onion on top of beans.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from tablespoon, 2-inches apart, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven about 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.
You can use sweet milk; reduce soda to 1/4 teaspoon and use 2 teaspoons baking powder.

title: texas style chili
directions: Combine ground chuck, sausage, onions, pepper and garlic in a Dutch oven; cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: sage stuffing
directions: Put 4 tablespoons of melted butter into skillet.
Add onion and celery and cook, stirring often, over moderate heat until vegetables are soft but not browned.
In large bowl, combine dried bread, sage, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add onion and celery mixture and remaining melted butter.
Toss until well mixed.
Using your hands works best for mixing.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and only use grease to brown flour.
Boil chicken. Cut up in a large boiler.
When tender, put celery and onions in and cook longer.
Spoon broth over into browned flour like gravy; then mix into your chicken pot.

title: katie's chicken
directions: Wash chicken and drain.
Place on a large, greased cookie sheet or pan.
Brush chicken with soup, dressing and apricot mixture until pieces are coated.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Brush mixture on chicken occasionally.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, milk, flour and egg yellows.
Beat egg whites and mix with other mixture.
Chop up Butterfingers in blender and add to milk mixture.
Dissolve Junket tablets in 1/4 cup cold water.
Pour everything in freezer with the Junket tablets being the last thing in.
Turn dasher 3 or 4 times and close up.
Let sit for 5 minutes before cranking.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine pineapple with juice, cherry pie filling, cornstarch, sugar and food coloring.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add dry Jell-O.
Cool.
Stir in bananas and nuts.
Put into pie shells and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: wassail
directions: Put allspice, cloves and cinnamon in a bag.
Place spices in saucepan with apple cider and brown sugar; simmer for 15 minutes. Yields 1 gallon.

title: pork with pineapple
directions: Slice pork crosswise into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in hot butter 5 minutes per side or until no longer pink.
Remove from skillet; cover and keep warm.
Add undrained pineapple and zucchini strips to skillet.
Bring to boiling, scraping up brown bits in skillet with a wooden spoon.
Boil 3 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
To serve, arrange pork on individual plates and top with sauce.

title: ice cream(hand crank)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients, stirring often, to make custard. Cool. Add vanilla and heavy cream.
Put in freezer, add milk to within one finger length of the top.
Put in beater, put on lid and crank.
Put in outside pail with ice and salt around it. Crank away!

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the first 3 ingredients. Cream together next 2 ingredients.
Gradually add next 2 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients; mix well.

title: philly pinwheels
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal. Spread with cream cheese.
Sprinkle with ham and olives.
Roll up, starting at short end; seal edges.
Cut each roll into 4 slices.
Place, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: turkey soup
directions: Add vegetables to broth and cook until nearly soft.
Add noodles and cook 10 more minutes.
Add meat; heat and serve.
If desired, you may add milk or cream of mushroom soup.
A good way to use turkey leftovers.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Freeze bread.
Remove from freezer and cut off crust.
Cut each slice into 5 finger size strips.
Put on cookie sheet in 200° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove and cool.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, apples and orange through food grinder (coarse attachment).
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add nuts and grapes.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: italian pork roast
directions: Cut pork roast in half and place in roasting bag combined with other ingredients.
Pour in Italian dressing.
Slow cook in roasting pan at 250 to 300 degrees for 3 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 to 9.

title: star spangled banana bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt, ginger and orange peel; mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until warm (120 to 130°, butter does not need to melt). Add to flour mixture; add egg and bananas.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled, about 1 hour.

title: honey egg white frosting
directions: Heat honey to 248° on candy thermometer or until a hard ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat; pour slowly into egg white.
Add lemon juice.
Continue beating until thick enough to hold its shape, about 5 minutes.
Spread on cake.
Dust lightly with cinnamon.

title: corn pie
directions: Melt butter in double boiler, add pimentos, cheese, egg, and corn.
Combine cracker crumbs and tomatoes, add to other ingredients.
Place in shallow baking dish, cover with additional cheese and bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef hash
directions: In a large pot cook ground beef, drain fat.
Then add all ingredients.
Let simmer until potatoes are done.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Preheat 2-quart saucepan; swirl oil in bottom of pan, then add pepper, celery and onion.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender (about 10 minutes).
Set aside.
Combine chicken broth, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir to a smooth paste.
In small saucepan, cook, then stir in brown sugar, pineapple and chicken and add vegetable mixture.
Heat over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.
Great over rice or noodles.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Soak raisins in warm water about 1 hour.
Drain and add sour cream, sugar, well beaten eggs, salt and cinnamon.
After the mixture is well mixed, pour into pie crust and bake until done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend 3 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until cookies are slightly brown, about 10 minutes.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water with salt and pepper to taste for 45 minutes; drain. When cool, slice or cut chicken and place in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Saute mushrooms in saucepan with margarine and a little pepper. Place mushrooms over chicken in dish. Pour 1 can undiluted chicken soup over mushrooms. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Set aside to dissolve.
Mix together 1 quart water, sugar, alum and salt.
Beat in 6 cups flour, vegetable oil and the yeast mixture. Knead in 6 more cups flour.
Put in greased bowl; grease top and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Put in greased bread pans. Prick with fork and let rise until double, about 1/2 hour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: western style beef-n-beans
directions: In a dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onion and celery until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender; drain. Dissolve bouillon in water.
Stir into beef mixture.
Add the beans, ketchup, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Stir.
Top with bacon.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all
together and bake 15 minutes at 425°,	then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sour cream until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in lemon juice, green onion, red pepper, milk and shrimp (reserve a few for garnish).
Season to taste with salt. Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, stir gently.
Turn into a serving dish and top with reserved shrimp and almonds.
Surround with a variety of crisp raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda, salt, Raisin Bran and sugar.
In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix together.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into each cup of buttered or paper lined muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter may be made in advance or kept chilled in air-tight container for up to 6 weeks.

title: cheese and onion cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions in butter.
Pour butter into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add corn muffin mix prepared as box directs, but substitute creamed corn for milk.
Turn into buttered dish.
Top with layered onions, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all together well.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake one hour at 350°.
Cool and slice.

title: wedding bells
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly and roll into inch balls. Preheat oven to 350° and bake 10 minutes or until light brown. While still warm, roll in sugar and shake excess off.
Serve warm or cool.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Prepare 1 stick of pie crust as directed and stir in cheese with hot water.
Roll out to 13 x 10-inches.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and cut into 3 strips lengthwise and then much smaller pieces crosswise (about 25).
Do not separate; they will bake apart.
Sprinkle with salt and seed.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400° to 450° or until golden brown.
Makes about 75.

title: tishy's hershey syrup sheet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add chocolate add mix well.
Stir in the beaten eggs a small amount at a time.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly.
Pour into a well greased 9 by 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool before frosting with icing recipe below.

title: cheese noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, sour cream, mashed cream cheese and vanilla.
Add noodles.
Pour into a large well buttered baking dish.
Spread crumbled corn flakes over the top.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soups and green chilies.
Heat, but do not boil.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortillas.
Put a layer of chicken, soup mixture, onion and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli in water 5 minutes and drain.
Saute onion and celery in 1/2 stick margarine.
Mix all ingredients and pour in a large, buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, flour, cocoa and egg yolks in saucepan. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and extract.
Pour in pie shell. Top with meringue and brown.

title: elegant crab meat spread
directions: Heat undiluted	soup;
mix
gelatine with 3 tablespoons water and
add
to
soup.
Stir until dissolved.	Add softened cream cheese
and
blend	well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold (1 large or 2 small).	Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres with crackers.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread chili over the cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over chili.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.

title: baked salmon filets with fennel and lemon
directions: Rinse salmon and pat dry.
Place in buttered, glass baking dish.
Rinse and slice fennel bulb and place on top of filets. Add lemon slices and onion/leek.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Pour maple syrup over both filets.
Bake in 350 degree oven approximately 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Veggies will be crunchy.
Serve with Mango Salsa, found in the Appetizers, Relishes and Pickles section of the cookbook.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Bring
ingredients
to
a boil and while hot, pour over torn, fresh spinach leaves.
Toss!
If desired, thin this with up to 1/3 cup water to give a milder taste.

title: carrot relish dish
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Mix in onion and pepper.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 8 to 12 hours.
Drain and serve.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: turkey puffs
directions: Mix turkey, onion, cream cheese and butter together.
Pinch dough together to make rectangles.
Place 2 large tablespoons of mixture on dough.
Fold and pinch together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray bottom only of 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pan. Beat butter in large bowl, add granulated sugar & brown sugar, beat well. Add egg, egg whites & vanilla. Beat until well blended. Add mashed bananas and beat. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, & baking powder in medium bowl. Add flour mixture to butter. Mix alternately with cream. Mix well. Pour batter evenly in loaf pan. Bake about 1 hour 15 minutes. Cool bread in pan on wire rack for about 10 minutes.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: Mix together with hands. Divide into 2 rolls and wrap in foil. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 225° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cold winter night casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and tomato soup, heat to bubbling.
Add cheese, Worcestershire sauce and parsley.
Simmer and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour noodles (uncooked if you wish) into greased 2 quart casserole.
Pour meat mixture over, and stir to mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 c margarine and 2 oz chocolate on high 1-2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut and chopped peanuts.
Press onto bottom of 9 x 13 pan and chill for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, chili powder, cumin and red pepper in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in salsa. Spread onto 10-inch serving platter lined with lettuce.
Top with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with chips. Makes 10 appetizer servings.

title: spicy mexican chicken halves
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Grill chicken halves, bone sides down, 5 inches from medium coals 20 to 30 minutes; turn chicken.
Grill 30 to 40 minutes longer, turning and brushing frequently with tomato mix until done.

title: reese's peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet or chill until firm enough to handle and shape into one-inch balls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: reeces peanut butter cups
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine, (can be done in the microwave) stir in powdered sugar.
When it gets too thick to stir, knead with hands.
Press out thinly on 2 cookie sheets. Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave, stirring often. The chocolate chips do not lose their form.
Spread mixture over the cookie.
Cool 3 minutes.
Slice & eat.

title: apple ring cucumber pickles(mock apple rings)
directions: Split cucumbers and remove seeds.
Slice to 1/4 inch thick. Soak for 24 hours in lime and water to cover.
Rinse well.

title: nippy cottage cheese dip
directions: Press cottage cheese through fine wire sieve.
Combine with yogurt and other ingredients.
Let stand for an hour or so for flavors to blend.
Serve in a chilled bowl surrounded by crisp, raw vegetables, cooked whole shrimp or Melba toast.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: to die for beef roast
directions: Place roast in crockpot. Mix contents of all 3 envelopes and sprinkle over roast. Pour water into the bottom of the crockpot. Cover and cook on LOW for 6 to 7 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; shape into little balls. Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve as an appetizer.
Makes about 50.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine the cracker crumbs and margarine. Place half of the mixture in a square 2-quart container.
Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Whip the topping and milk.
Mix with the cream cheese and sugar.
Spread half the whipped mixture over the graham cracker crumbs. Add the pie filling. Spread the remainder of the whipped mixture over the pie filling.
Top with remainder of the crumb mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add cream of mushroom and chicken soups, chicken broth and grated cheese. Remove
from heat and add spaghetti, chicken and salt and pepper to	taste.	Mix
and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish
for
30 minutes at 370°.
Add grated cheese and sprinkle on top last 10 minutes of baking.

title: chocolate scotch marble cake
directions: In large bowl, blend first 5 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour 2 cups of batter in another bowl.
Stir butterscotch bits into 1 mixture and chocolate in other.
Pour 1/2 of light batter in greased tube pan, then pour chocolate batter. Repeat using the light; marble by folding with knife in cutting motion.
Bake at 325° for 50 or 55 minutes.
Ice as you like.
I use sour cream icing.

title: crunchy pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Combine next three ingredients (crackers, pecans and baking powder).
Fold into egg whites. Spread in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in the center of preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread with whipped cream.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: sweet mustard chicken
directions: Wash, trim and julienne chicken into 1/2 x 1/2 x 4-inch strips. Place in saute pan with onions.
Use 1/2 ounce clarified butter. Saute chicken and onions until 80 percent done.
Don't overcook! Place saute into a casserole dish.
Ladle on honey mustard and place cheese on top.
Bake until sauce is hot and cheese is melted. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Will be very sticky.
Pat into baking dish and put in refrigerator until set.

title: red beans and rice salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans; set aside to drain.
Combine dressing and next 7 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill 2 hours.

title: broccoli-cheddar soup
directions: Saute the onion in the margarine.
Blend in the flour and salt.
Gradually add milk until thick.
Continue to stir while adding the cheese.
Add the cooked broccoli.
Stir and be careful not to scorch the bottom of the pan.
Serves 6.

title: pecan balls
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Roll into balls. Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: drunken turkey
directions: Coat turkey skin and cavity with butter.
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and garlic powder inside and outside.
Place turkey in a large roasting pan.
Cut onions and celery into 4-inch pieces.
Grate orange rind and set aside.
Peel orange and cut into sections.
Mix celery, onion and orange and stuff into cavity (or under breast).
Mix brandy, Triple Sec and wine together and pour over turkey.
Sprinkle rind over top and bake at 325° until done. The drippings can be used in cornbread dressing.
It's outstanding.

title: whole roasted garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Remove outer skin from garlic and arrange right side up in an 8 X 8 X 2 pan.
Drizzle oil over garlic, letting it run between cloves.
Cover and bake 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Cool to serve.
Pull off cloves and gently squeeze paste onto bread.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 12 pan with Pam. In large mixing bowl, combine cheeses, sour cream, half and half and butter. Heat in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes; stir and repeat.

title: crisp gingersnaps
directions: Add together margarine, molasses, sugar and eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves and add to first mixture.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix thoroughly with hands until mixture is smooth.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with olive oil.
Shape meat mixture into an oblong dish with rounded top. Only the bottom of the meat loaf should be touching the pan.
The sides and the top should be free to crisp.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake the meat loaf for 1 1/4 hours.
Slice each square piece of cheese in half to form eight triangles.
Starting in the middle, on top of the meat loaf, lay the pieces of cheese so that they overlap each other and the pointed sides go to the ends (4 pointed one way and 4 pointed the other way).
Put back in the oven so that the cheese melts.
Serve hot with mashed potatoes and gravy and your choice of vegetables and hot rolls.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to mixture.
Add flavoring last.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: refrigerator orange pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add milk, orange concentrate and orange peel.
Pour into crust.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Garnish with orange slices just prior to serving.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of juice.
In mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion.
Mixture will be sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to juice.
Form into small patties. Roll in flour and fry in hot oil about five minutes or until golden brown.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in covered jar. Makes about 1 1/4 pints of mix.

title: easy 7 layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the ingredients in order.
Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: new hummingbird cake(makes 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-inch tube cake pan with floured, non-stick baking spray.
In large bowl, mix together sifted flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Make a well in center and put in yolks, oil, vanilla and pineapple.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Fold in bananas and pecans.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
(Double recipe for 13 x 9-inch pan.)

title: whipped lemon pound cake
directions: Let butter and eggs stand at room temperature for 1/2 hour. Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg.
Beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Add flour and cream alternately to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Beat in lemon extract.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: rhubarb dessert #1
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cup flour, margarine, oatmeal and brown sugar.
Pat 1/2 of this in 9 x 13 pan.
Cook rhubarb, sugar and 5 Tbsp. flour. Put this over the above ingredients.
Put strawberry Jell-O powder over next.
Then put rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm as appetizers.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Nuts may also be added.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 cup quick cooking oatmeal. Set aside to cool while you prepare batter. Add all the ingredients well. Then mix oats mixture. Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dip or cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix altogether.
Sprinkle with dill weed or Salad Supreme (if desired).
Can do ahead.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jb's caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a very large kettle (like a water bath kettle). Bring sugar, margarine and syrup to a boil in a very heavy pan. Pour over popped corn. Mix well. Spread mixture on cookie sheets and bake at 200 degrees until dry (about 2 - 2 1/2 hours). Enjoy!

title: sister's cheese cake
directions: Cream the sugar, flavoring and cheese.
Add dissolved Jell-O and mix well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini, boil and drain.
Set aside.
Lightly saute (do not brown) onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Add zucchini.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake until melted.

title: tiella(italian cheesecake; a hot dish, not a dessert)
directions: Beat eggs very well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Pour into a well-greased large bowl.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then lower oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Bake until a golden crust forms.

title: spinach bread dip
directions: Hollow out bread, making a bowl with 1-inch sides.
Cut removed bread in small chunks.
Mix remaining ingredients and chill several hours.
Serve in bread with bread chunks and fresh vegetables all around.
When dip is gone, break "bread bowl" into chunks and enjoy.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix well and roll small balls in coconut.
Very good recipe!

title: margaret mundahl's norwegian meatballs
directions: Soak breadcrumbs in milk.
Add beaten egg and seasonings; mix well with raw meat.
Form into balls (about the size of 1 tablespoon measure) and brown in skillet.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until well blended.
Stir into the flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Slice steak into 2 by 2 pieces. Heat oil in a large skillet or dutch oven to medium. Add meat and brown slightly. Add flour mixing until evenly coated. Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook until
meat appears done. Add enough
of the water to make a gravy. Add the bay leaf and simmer for 45 minutes. Remove the bay leaf and add the mushrooms. Cook for 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from heat and add the
sauce and the sour cream. Let stand 5 minutes. Serve
over noodles, mashed potatoes or rice. Serves 6.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and wash cucumbers; slice very thin.
Place in china (or glass) bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze cukes dry.
(If it gets too watery, pour some off.)
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the cukes.
Mix well and serve.

title: horseradish sauce for beef
directions: Combine all well.
Store in closed container in the refrigerator.
Great with pot roast and any other cut of beef.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Line large casserole dish with ground beef.
Layer potatoes, onion and season with salt and pepper.
Mix soups and carrots together and pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Real good.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak the roast overnight covered with water, 4 tablespoons of vinegar and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Drain water off and rinse several times.
Cover roast with flour generously and brown in fat on both sides; add remainder of seasonings and 3/4 cup of water.
Simmer with lid on for 1 hour.
Add remaining water; simmer until tender. You may have to add more water if it cooks out.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Note: Fewer may be required.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken on rice and onion soup mix.
Mix 1 can soup with 3 cups water.
Pour on chicken.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger or sausage in skillet and drain off grease. Mix all ingredients together in a crock pot until very hot. Serve with taco chips.

title: romanian beef sausages(carnatzlach)
directions: Combine all ingredients except the club soda, and mix well, kneading with your hands so it becomes compact.
Add soda gradually, kneading between additions until the dough is smooth, fine and almost elastic.
Wet the palms of your hands and roll portions of the mixture into sausage like cylinders, each about 3/4 to 1-inch thick and 3 to 4-inches long.
Arrange in a single layer on a platter and cover with wax paper or foil.
Chill for at least 5 hours, but preferably 24, to develop the flavor.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before cooking.
Broil for about 10 minutes, turning frequently so all sides brown.
Turn with tongs or a wood spatula so the sausages don't break.
These are also good on the he bare.
Makes six servings.

title: east bank steak and gravy
directions: Put steak in a 4 to 5-quart baking dish or pan, along with other ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until tender.

title: pomegranate jelly
directions: Prepare juice.
Cut 10 to 12 fully ripe pomegranates in half; ream on an orange juicer.
Place in jelly cloth or bag and squeeze out juice.
Measure 4 cups into very large saucepan.
Add exact amount of sugar to juice.
Mix well.
Place over high heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
At once, stir in Certo. Bring to a full boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; skin off foam with metal spoon and pour quickly into jars.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch of hot paraffin.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine
egg yolks, sugar, flour, lemon juice and lemon rind in	top
of
double
boiler.
Stir	in 1 1/2 cups boiling water; cook
over	medium	heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in	butter.
Cool, then pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until
soft
peaks form.
Add sugar to sweeten and vanilla (gradually), beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue over
filling.
Bake at 425° until meringue is delicately browned.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn warm in oven.

title: ratatouille
directions: Skin tomatoes by placing them in boiling water for 10 seconds. Slice eggplant into 1/4 inch slices.
Slice onion thinly.
Roughly slice green peppers.
Peel garlic cloves.
Thinly slice zucchini. Heat oil in a large shallow pan.
Fry onion until golden.
Add crushed garlic and green pepper.
Add eggplant and zucchini.
Fry vegetables gently.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover pan and simmer 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Heat thoroughly.
Dust with parsley.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Set sausage out to soften. Mix all 3 ingredients with hands in large bowl. Form into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef bones in water until meat is done, several hours. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are done. More water may be needed.

title: honey drops
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add honey and vanilla.
Sift in flour and soda.
Chill until firm.
Form into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Place apricot jam between 2 cooled cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: *May also use fresh vegetables.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and mash.
Blend in sandwich spread, salt and pepper.
Refill whites.

title: spoon bill
directions: Soak fish in cooking wine for 1 to 2 hours.
Rinse.
Scramble 2 eggs with a little water.
Put fish in eggs and water batter.
Then season fish with Creole seasoning and flour.

title: chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet with onion.
Drain.
Add to other ingredients.
Put in a large pot on warm to medium heat. Cook slowly for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: mushroom wild rice
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water, wild rice, butter, and 1/2 tsp. salt to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 40 minutes. Stir in brown rice. Cover and simmer 25-30 minutes longer or until rice is tender. Mean while, in a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon to paper towels; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. In the drippings, saute mushrooms, onion, pepper, and celery until tender. Stir in broth and remaining salt. Bring to boil. Combine the cornstarch and cold water until smooth; stir into the mushroom mixture. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly; stir in almonds and bacon. Drain rice; add mushroom mixture. Transfer to a greased 13x9 baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Uncover; bake 5-10 minutes longer or until heated through. Yield: 12 servings.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand 1 hour.
Makes 2 cups. This is a recipe for a Seder at Passover.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender.
Good for coleslaw or fruit salad.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, cinnamon, allspice (in a bag) all together.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stick two whole cloves in each peach half.
Add peach halves to hot spiced syrup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool, covered.
Chill 24 hours. Remove spices.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt margarine and add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Make into balls and put a chocolate chip on top of each ball. Do not bake, just put on wax paper to set.

title: joann's american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In large frying pan, cook ground beef, green pepper, onion, celery and mushrooms until vegetables are tender and meat is browned; drain off fat.
Add crushed tomatoes, beef bouillon cubes, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in cooked macaroni and simmer on low 15 to 20 minutes.

title: delicious angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Cool and cut cake into 2 layers.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except pie filling.
Frost cake with mixture.
Top frosted cake with pie filling.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Mix rice and rest of ingredients except parsley in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put chicken on top of rice and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tinker cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Put water, margarine, oil and cocoa in sauce pan and mix well.
Bring to a boil;
pour over dry ingredients, mix well and set aside.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add to the chocolate mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 ijnch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until done Test with a toothpick for doneness. Frost while warm.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Put 1 can Hershey's syrup in pan.
Break candy bars and put in syrup to melt.
Let melt and add other can of syrup and let cool. Cream
sugar
and
Crisco.	Add
eggs and chocolate mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk and add to batter alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake
in	tube
pan
for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shiitake-sesame vinaigrette with basmati rice
directions: Garnish with edible flowers in season or sweet red peppers.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best ever apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over apples and mix.
Add melted butter.
Mix thoroughly so all apples are coated.
Put in a 9-inch square pan.

title: joseph's sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, egg and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in granulated sugar in small bowl.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, bake for 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Makes approximately 50 cookies.

title: rum pudding pie with coconut crust
directions: Mix butter with 2 2/3 cups coconut.
Press in 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Boil ribs for 45 minutes and drain.
Place ribs in baking pan and cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on one side; turn and repeat on other side.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, except pineapple.
Mix pineapple, bananas and lemon juice together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well and keep refrigerated.

title: potato crusted chicken
directions: Season chicken with your favorite seasoning blend (Cajun, Creole, etc.).
Spread light coating of mustard on one side of chicken.
Heat olive oil in skillet. Peel potato and grate. Pat grated potato onto mustard side of chicken.
Place chicken in hot skillet, potato side up.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Flip chicken another 3 to 4 minutes.
Flip again and cook until chicken is done.

title: miniwaki (beer cheese soup)
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute vegetables until limp; do not brown.
Stir flour into vegetables and continue stirring over low heat until flour expands.
Add chicken broth, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in cheeses and beer, stirring until cheese melts.
Add seasonings and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake according to the directions on the box.
Make Jell-O using 1/2 the amount of water called for.
Mix the pudding according to directions.
Bake cake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool, then poke holes in top of cake with a fork.
Pour the Jell-O over the cake, filling the holes.
Spread the pudding over the top of the cake and cover with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate fantasy cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 2-inch round pan and set aside.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread 1 cup of stuffing mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except reserved stuffing and spread on top.
Sprinkle top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; beat until smooth. Spread over the tortillas. Sprinkle with onion. Top with turkey and spinach. Roll up tightly jellyroll style. Serve immediately. Yield: 10 servings (I cut in half).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in a pizza pan and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread on top of cookie dough.
Top with fruit and nuts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender (approximately 10 minutes). Combine sour cream and chicken soup; mix well and set aside.
Mix stuffing and melted butter; reserve 1/3 cup for topping.
Drain veggies and add soup mix and stuffing.
Mix well.
Pour mix in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: "no sage" chicken and dressing
directions: Simmer onion and celery in 2 cups broth 15 minutes until almost clear.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben dinner casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner.
Increase the milk to 1/2 cup.
Put half of the mix in a casserole.
Chop up corned beef and spread over top of cheese mix.
Put Swiss cheese slices on the meat.
Put drained sauerkraut over the cheese and put remaining macaroni dinner on top and bake for 25 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: egg nog(this is a good holiday drink.)
directions: To make an ice ring for the punch, use a tube pan and fill halfway with water.
Freeze, but before it is totally frozen, decorate with strawberry leaves and pieces of fruit.
When needed, remove ice from pan and you will have a beautifully decorated ice ring.

title: clark's oatmeal rolls
directions: Place yeast in a small bowl with warm water.
In an extra large bowl put oats, boiling water, molasses, shortening and salt. Cool this to lukewarm.
Stir yeast and add beaten eggs, mixing well.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time, mixing well.
Add a little more flour if it feels too thin.
Grease top of the mixture and let rise for 2 hours.
Shape into rolls and place in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yummy!

title: apple pie pecans
directions: Mix
apples, sugar and cinnamon in a 8-inch square pan. Put pecans over apples.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and flour. Put over apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken bits
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Dip into beaten eggs and then roll into bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until lightly brown.
Serve hot with any flavor dressing.

title: orange slush salad
directions: Bring sugar and 2 1/2 cups water to a boil. Add pineapple, frozen orange juice and 1 can water (use the can from your frozen orange juice to measure water).
Mix real good.
Let mixture cool somewhat before adding bananas. Freeze.

title: venison jerky
directions: Slice venison into strips 3/8-inch thick to ensure total saturation of meat while marinating.

title: robertson's fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Drain other fruit, but do not save juice.
Stir 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice into pudding mix. Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; cook until thick. Let cool and pour over fruit.

title: basic squash casserole
directions: Brown onions in half of margarine.
Add to remaining ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Put Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: crunchy ice cream
directions: Best to double first 5 ingredients.
Mix all together well. Press 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 gallon ice cream, then spread remaining half on top.
Keep frozen.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix together ingredients and add to chopped apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef, drain.
Put in mixing bowl. Add cheese and oregano mix.
Add tomato sauce.
Spread on slices of party rye.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
This can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Line greased 2-quart casserole with 2/3 of the dressing.
