Place chicken over this.
Mix soups and broth together; pour over chicken.
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brazil nut crab salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine crabmeat, celery and nuts.
In small bowl, mix chili sauce, mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and salt.
Pour over crab; toss.
Refrigerate.
At serving time, skin, pit and slice avocados.
Dip into 6 tablespoons lemon juice. Arrange crab salad on serving dish; garnish with avocados.
Makes 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Drain pineapple.
Retain juice and mix with sugar, bring to a boil.
Boil until the sugar dissolves.
Poke holes in the baked cake (using the handle of a wooden spoon works well).
Pour the juice into the holes.
Spread the crushed pineapple on top of the cake, then add the cooked pudding.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle on coconut, if desired.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cook broccoli until soft.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, soups and curry powder.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken, mayonnaise mixture, croutons, butter and cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: sausage foo yung(a chinese breakfast treat)
directions: Boil rice until ready; when rice is ready, fry the rice in a skillet.
Add bean sprouts and fry onions separately (from the rice).
Then scramble the eggs and cook them in skillet, with the bean sprouts and onions.
When everything is prepared, including the fried rice, set all of the cooked ingredients on the side.
Now you are ready to cook the sausage (Sloppy Joe-style).
When the sausage has been thoroughly cooked (well done), mix the sausage in with the rice, onion, eggs and bean sprouts.
Then re-cook all of the ingredients at a low flame.
When the Sausage Foo Yung appears to be ready, you might want to spice it up with your favorite seasonings; but it might be better to leave it as it is (to keep that Chinese flavor).

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Combine popcorn and almonds in a large bowl.
In 4 cup measuring cup, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes longer until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn mix and mix well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Spread on foil or waxed paper to cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie crust.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate.
May also be frozen.

title: watermelon slush
directions: In large saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Bring to boiling, stirring, until sugar is dissolved; boil gently uncovered 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit punch until dissolved. In a blender, combine about 1/2 cubed watermelon and lemon juice; blend until smooth.
Repeat with remaining cubed watermelon; stir into fruit punch mixture.
Turn mixture into a freezer container. Chill 8 hours or until firm.

title: rotel king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In a large pan, saut pepper and onions in margarine until tender.
Add soups, tomatoes and chicken stirring until well blended.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, alternate layer of tortillas, soup mixture and cheese, repeating for 3 layers.
Bake 40 minutes until hot and bubbling.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cover catfish in water; cook until meat will separate from bone.
Remove catfish from stock (reserve stock).
Use a 3 gallon pot.
Saute onions in oil.
Add potatoes and cover with fish stock.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Cook Karo, sugar and cream to a soft ball on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts, coconut and corn flakes.
Spread on a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, add cream cheese, beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then stir in sour cream, lemon peel and juice.
Put 3/4 cup into a small bowl, stir in 1/2 cup lemon curd. Pour 1/2 remaining filling into pan.
Then pour on curd mixture and then remaining filling on top of that.
Bake for 1 hour at 325 degrees.
Cool on rack for 20 minutes.
Spread with rest of lemon curd, chill and serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bakes in about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, egg, milk and shortening.
Add blueberries and stir carefully.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: zucchini casserole i
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing and seasoning.
Saute onion and zucchini 10 minutes or until tender.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots together.
In bottom of casserole dish put 1/2 of the zucchini mix, then 1/2 of the stuffing mix, then 1/2 of the soup and sour cream mix.
Repeat for 2nd layer.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix until blended.
Put in 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, butter or margarine and milk and bring to a boil; boil 1 minute (no longer).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool.
Remove with spatula from wax paper.
Ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spoon out of bowl with teaspoon. Roll each ball onto sugar on plate.
Spread out on a cookie sheet with a fork in a cross.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit on clouds
directions: Beat the egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla until bubbly. Add sugar gradually and beat until stiff.
Add crackers and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350°
for 25 minutes. Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and pie filling.

title: tomatoes in foil or pan in oven
directions: For Foil:
Will need 2 large pieces of heavy duty foil.
Spray foil with Pam spray.

title: kay's quick dessert
directions: Mix package of instant pudding with Cool Whip.
Mix in the canned fruit.

title: italian coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks and butter together, then add to flour, soda, buttermilk, coconut, pecans and vanilla mixture.
Fold in 5 egg whites.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Whisk pudding mix into milk.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of the topping and rest of the strawberries.
Spread over gelatin. Chill until set, about 2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Grease and flour cake pan or bread pans.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg and banana.
Add flour, milk and soda.
Blend thoroughly, but don't over mix.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes then remove.

title: skillet fried cabbage
directions: Preheat oil in skillet. Slice cabbage into hot oil. Add diced tomatoes, diced green pepper and celery. Stir all together. Add salt and pepper to taste. Lower heat to low. Let simmer until done, about 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix together egg and water; add vinegar and lard.
To this add rest of ingredients.
Mix until a smooth dough is formed.
Makes 5 crusts.
Freeze or refrigerate until needed.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When ready to use, thaw and line crust with white of an egg.
This keeps it from leaking.

title: sunrise smoothie(breakfast shake)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
With blender on high, add ice cubes, one at a time, processing until smooth after each addition.
Serve immediately. Makes about 2 cups.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until lightly brown.
Add soups and mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Put cheese on top of meat mixture. Put Tater Tots on top of cheese.
Bake until potatoes are brown.

title: mexicorn lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add corn, tomato sauce, picante sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer, stirring frequently, 5 minutes. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan, oregano and garlic salt; mix well.
Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with half of meat mixture.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange remaining tortillas over cheese. Top with remaining meat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: halusky(drop dumplings)
directions: You will need 1 large pan for boiling salted water.

title: clara's fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas in a large bowl.
Pour can of apricot pie filling to cover bananas.
Add thawed frozen peaches and strawberries.
Mix and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in 2 1/2 or 3 quart casserole dish. Bake,
covered,
in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover
and sprinkle
with
buttered
bread crumbs (Pepperidge Farm).	Let brown.
Serves 12.

title: my favorite mexican dip
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Drain chilies; gently stir in chilies, tomato and onion.
Put in serving bowl; chill.
Serve with taco chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, hollow out middle of loaf of bread.
Fill with dip.
Cut remaining bread into large cubes and use as dippers.

title: darlene's pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes enough for several pies.
It freezes real well and is a very rich crust, but good!

title: crab dip
directions: In double boiler, blend cheese and butter.
Add everything else.
Heat together (a la fondue).
Serve with crackers.
This stuff is great!
Another recipe from New Orleans dorm roommate. Good for New Orleans Saints football parties.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In medium bowl, toss strawberries with sugar and liqueur or juice.
Let stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally, about 30 minutes.
With long serrated knife cut cake horizontally into 3 equal layers.
Spread half of jam over cut side of bottom layer. Replace middle layer and cover with remaining jam.
Add top layer. Cut reassembled cake into 3/4-inch slices.
To assemble trifle, line bottom and sides of 1 1/2-quart glass serving bowl with about 2/3 of jam-filled cake slices.
Drizzle about 1/4 cup of juice from berries over cake.
Spoon half of vanilla custard over cake and spread half of strawberries over custard.
Cover with remaining cake slices; drizzle with remaining berry juice and top with remaining custard and berries.
Cover trifle and refrigerate up to 6 hours before serving.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into bottom of pie crust.
Make pudding according to directions for pie.
Pour over bananas.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
You can also use coconut on top instead of whipped topping.
Can also use chocolate pudding instead of vanilla.

title: brunch cheese casserole
directions: Trim off bread crusts.
Butter slices and cut in 1-inch cubes. Toss in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Add cheese and diced ham.
Beat eggs and blend with milk.
Add salt.
Pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Nice with fruit cup and bran muffins.

title: scripture cake
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients together well. Sift the next 4 ingredients together and add alternately with the next ingredient. Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy (Proverbs 23:14). Add the next 3 ingredients. Fold in the beaten yolks and stiffly beaten whites carefully. Bake in a lined 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fluffy chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and milk, reserving 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken; sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: rice salad
directions: Put rice in serving bowl and pour 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 4 tablespoons vinaigrette over.
Add freshly ground black pepper to taste.
Toss well with fork.
Prepare all the remaining ingredients, except tomato and cucumber and blend.
Mix well and let cool.
Add tomato and cucumber just before serving to maintain best texture and taste for those two vegetables.
Yield:
4 serving.
Carbohydrate 37 g, protein 5 g, fat .7 g, calories 170.

title: peanut butter cookies(quick and easy)
directions: Mix peanut butter and milk until creamy.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar. Place approximately 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Bake until only slightly browned (do not overbake.)
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and coconut; mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Chop onion, parsley and cabbage.
Grate carrots.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with combined vegetables and seasonings.
Combine soup and salad dressing; mix well.
Gradually add water to soup mixture, mixing until well blended.
Pour half the soup mix over vegetables.
Top with chicken and remaining soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roast pheasant
directions: Rub inside with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place strips of bacon on bird.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven at 325° until tender, about 1 hour.
Baste often.

title: ham brown quiche
directions: Press thawed potatoes between paper towels and fit into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and fill with cheeses and ham.
Beat cream, eggs and salt together.
Pour over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well together and store in airtight container.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs, molasses and vinegar.
Mix dry ingredients; add to other mixture.
Roll into balls; put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Cook onion in butter and sausage and cook 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from fire.
After boiling chestnuts until soft, drain and add to first mixture.
Blend all ingredients and stuff bird lightly.

title: holiday sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and water; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half; chill 1 hour. On floured surface, roll dough 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in desired shapes and brush with milk.
Decorate with sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Let raisins and boiling water stand together overnight.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add shallot tops and parsley.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add crawfish and cook for 20 minutes.
Add rice; mix and set aside.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water then mix with yogurt and Cool Whip and put in pie shell. Chill and serve.

title: pecan crunch
directions: Mix eggs in a bowl.
Add sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and salt to eggs.
Beat until light.
Stir in pecan halves and pieces.

title: skillet strawberry cookies
directions: In skillet, combine dates, coconut, sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Cook over medium-low heat until mixture thickens, 5 or 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in Rice Krispies cereal, walnuts and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: hot boiled peanuts
directions: Put peanuts in crock-pot.
Put in water to cover.
Salt to taste.
Cook in crock-pot 12 to 15 hours on high for 1/2 hour, then low for remainder.
Peanuts should be soft and hot!

title: sweet-n-sour chicken or pork
directions: Wash and peel carrots.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Wash mushrooms and cut in half.
Dice bell pepper and onion.
Wash meat and cut into bite-size pieces.
Drain all water off.
Heat very large skillet or wok.
Put in oil, carrots, onion, bell pepper and meat.
Cover and cook until carrots start to tender and meat is done, stirring often.
Drain well, then add mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cook until almost done.
Add sauce and simmer until vegetables and meat are done.
Serve over rice.

title: pasta salad with tuna and snow peas
directions: Blanch snow peas 45 seconds in boiled, salted water.
Drain and refresh under cold running water.
Cut diagonal into 1/2-inch pieces and set aside.
Chop scallions finely.
Put tuna in large bowl and flake with fork.
Add snow peas, scallions, pasta and toss.
Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard and dill.
Add pasta mixture and toss well.
The mayonnaise mixture will be barely visible.
Add black pepper to taste.
Refrigerate approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: crazy apple pie
directions: Melt stick of margarine in baking dish (3-quart size) in oven. Mix milk, sugar and self-rising flour (looks like pancake batter) in a bowl.

Take out hot pan of melted margarine, pour the mix (sugar, milk and flour), dunk the apple filling into the mix in pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted margarine (don't stir).
Add peaches with juice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: "t" cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, oil and flavorings.
Add sugar and flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: easy s'mores(children's)
directions: Poke one chocolate chip into a miniature marshmallow (desired amount).
Put on plate and microwave until soft.
Scoop up with a graham cracker.

title: german chocolate pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 13 x 9-inch pan in 2 cups of boiling water. Add cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Chill until set. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: 3 hour oven stew
directions: Place prepared meat and vegetables in a large roasting pan with a tight fitting lid.
Stir to coat with the celery soup and tomato sauce; no other seasoning is required.
Place lid on and bake in oven at 325° for 3 hours.
No need to peek until the last 20 minutes or so to add the frozen peas or beans.
Everything goes into the pan raw, including the meat!
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: old fashion corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat well several times.
Then bake at 425° or 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour into 13 x 9 casserole dish. Top with bacon strips. Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes into Wesson oil and place in a baking pan. Sprinkle all sides with seasoned salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook celery, onion and pepper in margarine.
Add soups, broth, chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
Mix with chicken and spaghetti. Put in large pan and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put in oven until cheese bubbles.
This would be good frozen and add cheese when time to bake.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer chicken, soup and sour cream combined, crackers and 1/2 of the poppy seed.
Make 2 layers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture dropped in cold water turns brittle.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites. Add nuts and flavoring.
Beat until mixture begins to get stiff. Drop with teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble a tube of Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle 1/2 cracker mixture in 9-inch square Pyrex.
Pour melted oleo on cracker mixture.
Stir cream of chicken with cup up pieces of chicken.
Stir in small carton of sour cream.
Pour in Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle other cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eduardo's meringues
directions: Beat at low speed the egg whites for 20 minutes until raised. Add sugar little by little with a tablespoon.
Add vanilla last. Place them with a tablespoon an inch apart on a baking sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Could add food color (2 to 3 drops) to color them.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well and shape into rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in hot oven (425°) until light brown.

title: dry beans with ham hock
directions: Pick and wash about 2 cups dry beans of your choice.
Place in crock-pot with the ham hock.
Add water about 2 inches above the beans in pot.
Cook about 30 minutes on high, then reduce heat to low and cook 4 to 6 hours, stirring at intervals and adding water as needed.
Salt to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend well.
Beat on medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Punch holes in cake with toothpick or fork.
Pour other half of can of cream of coconut over top of cake while hot.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip (9 ounces) and sprinkle with coconut.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Before cooking, make a hole in center of meat loaf and put the heel of a loaf of bread to absorb the grease.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cream.
Sift and add flour, soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Test doneness with toothpick.

title: simple salad
directions: Use gelatin in powdered form for this recipe.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a jello mold and refrigerate.

title: ham rolls
directions: Beat the cheese with grated onion, horseradish, Worcestershire and wine until creamy.
Spread cheese mixture on boiled ham slices; roll slices up neatly and chill.
Cut into inch-long sections and "toothpick" before serving.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: meat potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup, potatoes and water. Bake in a casserole at 350° until potatoes are done.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Brown for 10 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw dough.
Roll thawed bread dough in rectangle, length of the cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 of preceeding ingredients in order listed on each rectangle.
Tuck ends of dough in and fold each side to center.
Place seam side down, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Grease dough slightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer, then repeat the following:
Crumble 1 cake layer, 1 can pineapple, 1 package strawberries, half the bananas, half the pudding mix and half the pecans.
All the Cool Whip goes on top.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Whip the cream.
Beat cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla slowly to the cream cheese.
Fold all ingredients together, except cherries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add beaten eggs and sugar.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour, ending with flour last.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° until leaves sides of pan or tests done.

title: to die for pie
directions: Melt candy bars in double boiler.
Add as many almonds that you want and 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Stir and put in Oreo cookie pie crust.
Add the rest of the Cool Whip.
Top with some more almonds and Magic Shell topping and then freeze it for a few hours or overnight.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut the breast into small chunks.
Put them into a bowl and pour 3/4 of the dressing over it.
Make sure the chicken is covered in it.
Then put lid over it, put in the fridge.
Let it set overnight or for how long you want to.

title: joel's spoon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine shortening and margarine, sugar and egg; add to yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover bowl with a damp towel or plastic wrap and place in refrigerator.
When ready to use, stir dough down and fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, or you can cut them out.

title: barbecued glazed chicken
directions: Brush chicken quarters with oil.
Salt and pepper.
Grill chicken, skin side up, on uncovered grill about 45 minutes or until tender (when a fork can easily be inserted).
Turn often.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer.

title: onion papooses
directions: Carefully spread room temperature cream cheese on thinly sliced beef or ham (processed sliced, ready to eat type).
Place green onion at one end of the meat slice and wrap meat around onion, pressing to seal at finished end.
Eat and enjoy.

title: terry's white clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta ahead.
Drain clams, reserving the liquid.
Mix white wine, broth and cornstarch to clam juice and set aside. Saute garlic and onions in oil.
Do not scorch.
Add liquid and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add clams, salt, pepper and thyme. Cook all only long enough to heat clams.
Do not overcook.

title: no-bake fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into roll.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Thaw and slice when needed.

title: reese's peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt cocoa and butter together and add sugar and mix well. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Sift flour and salt and stir into other ingredients.
Fill cupcakes 2/3 full and put peanut butter cup in middle and push down until even with dough. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: german string beans
directions: Cut string beans into bite-size pieces and boil in salt water until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp, add onions (cut in rings) to bacon dripping and well drained beans, vinegar and sugar; mix well.
Add crumbled crispy bacon and serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add shortening and eggs.
Beat well. Add applesauce and 1/2 cup pecans and beat slightly.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over cake dough in the pan the 2 tablespoons of sugar, 1/2 cup pecans and 1 cup chocolate chips. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: gone for the day roast
directions: Mix soup straight out of the can with dry gravy mix.
Pepper roast to taste.
(Do not salt; gravy adds plenty of salt.)
Top roast with soup and gravy mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake in oven on low.
No worry for about 4 hours.
If more time is needed, put roast on to cook still frozen.
When done, roast will be tender and juicy.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on a tray or pretty serving dish.
Mix together sauces and pour over top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with toppings of your choice.
Serve with nacho chips or tortilla chips.

title: chocolate fudge dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir or whisk until smooth.
Makes about 3/4 cup.
Great for dipping strawberries!

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion together.
Drain beans and mix into meat mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: blanc mange
directions: Scald 2 1/4 cups of milk.
Combine and blend well 3/4 cup milk, 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch.
Add to hot milk.
Stir and cook over low heat (or double boiler) until thickened.
Beat egg with rest of sugar.
Pour some hot mixture into egg and then back into hot liquid.
Stir until it thickens.
Cool; add vanilla. Chill.
Can serve with crushed fruit, chocolate, melted chocolate, brown sugar for butterscotch.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and slice, leaving skin on.
Place sliced apples on a large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Wrap foil tightly and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat margarine, cocoa and cola until mixture boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
(Marshmallows will remain on top of batter and melt when baked.)
Beat well; pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes at 350.
Frost while hot.

title: marinade for halibut or swordfish
directions: Marinate for 2 hours.
Then grill and brush with marinade sauce.
The fish is very moist.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt, 12 tablespoons of sugar and pepper.
Boil for a few minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add vinegar. While warm, add sliced cucumbers and onion rings.
Add 1/4 teaspoon of dried parsley, if desired.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw pie crust and place on flat cookie sheet.
Prick bottom and sides of crust with fork.
Combine milk, seasonings and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Add cheese and spinach.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add lemon juice to blueberry pie filling.
Pour over baked crumbs and top with Cool Whip.
Good festive dessert.

title: bulgar-rice pilaf
directions: Can vary spices and chopped veggies to taste.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix well and spread on roll.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream meringue pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan or top of double boiler, combine all the first eight ingredients and stir until smooth.
Turn up heating unit to medium high; bring mixture to a boil.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, to avoid sticking or scorching. Remove from heat.
Pour hot filling into baked crust.
Spread with prepared meringue, sealing edges to crust.
Sprinkle with flaked coconut.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in the Ranch dip packet.
Chop bell pepper.
Chop cilantro.
Spread cream cheese mix on tortilla. Sprinkle chopped bell pepper over cream cheese.
Sprinkle green chilies over.
Sprinkle grated cheese and cilantro.
Roll tortilla and secure with a toothpick.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, usually makes 4 Roll-Ups.
Wrap each in aluminum foil and chill at least 3 hours.
Slice before serving.
Serve with salsa.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix cheeses with beaten eggs.
Stir in flour until smooth. Add spinach until well blended.
Bake at 350° in 1-quart casserole sprayed with vegetable oil.
Bake one hour.
Cool about 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread(best)
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Alternately add flour and salt with sour milk and soda. Add bananas and walnuts. Pour into greased loaf pan that has bottom lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 1 or more hours.
When tests done, let set on rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 12.

title: chewy cocoa and peanut butter treats
directions: Stir together corn syrup and brown sugar in large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chips, cocoa and butter; stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
(Mixture will be thick.) Stir in cereal until coated.
Immediately press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 30 treats.

title: one-step chocolate cake
directions: Mix all at once.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(You cannot taste the coffee!)
Very moist cake.

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Cut a slice off the top of the bread (cut about 1/3 of the way down).
Set aside.
Hollow out loaf to form a crust shell.
Tear enough of the center to make 2 cups of cubes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all together and make into cakes.
Fry until lightly brown in a little oil.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put half of bread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole, then add half of cheese and half of sausage.
Complete this procedure with the other half of ingredients.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour this mixture over bread mixture in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup with small amount of milk and spread on top of casserole. Canned mushrooms can be added.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork chops and cook until they are almost done.
Take out of pan and make gravy with the pan drippings.
Then add 1 heaping tablespoon of applesauce (mix well with gravy).
After the gravy is made, add 1 large can of sauerkraut.
Stir ingredients well.
Pour into long baking dish (13 x 9-inch, preferably glass but doesn't need to be).
Then lay the 6 pork chops on top, pushing them down in, just a little.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs; add vanilla.
Then add buttermilk and flour.
Continue mixing.
Add bananas and nuts. Pour batter into a waxed and greased pan.
Let rest for a few minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes in 9 x 6 x 3-inch pan.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, chicken broth, soy sauce and garlic powder; set aside.
In a wok, put 2 tablespoons vegetable oil and stir-fry chicken until browned.
Set aside.
Put remaining tablespoon of oil in wok and add vegetables; stir-fry until tender but crisp.
Reduce heat to medium combine all ingredients in wok and cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve over rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until all dry ingredients are moist.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with firm crackers.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix with green beans and undiluted tomato soup in casserole.
Cover casserole with mashed potatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: canadian brown bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl and let cool until lukewarm; stir the mixture.
Mix the yeast, lukewarm water and sugar and set aside until it rises.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add white flour.
When you have added 4 to 5 cups, add liquid shortening.
Continue to mix until the dough is just a little bit sticky.
Cover with waxed paper and a towel.
Let rise and punch down 3 times.
Put in greased bread pans and let rise until doubled.
Grease tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 3/4 hour.
Makes 10 loaves.

title: spicy chicken-peanut pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions.
Saute onions, garlic and peppers until onions are transparent.
Add chicken; cook over medium heat for approximately 5 minutes.
Mix peanut butter, soy sauce and lemon juice and add to chicken mixture, continually cooking over medium heat.
Stir until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add cucumbers.
Cook one additional minute.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately over pasta.

title: mandarin and pineapple orange salad
directions: Make jello according to package directions and when it starts to set, add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into oiled mold and refrigerate until set.
When ready to serve, unmold on bed of red lettuce leaves and garnish with fresh mint.

title: strawberry valentine pie
directions: Blend cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in berries and their syrup.
Pour in shell and freeze.

title: salsa
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix the tomatoes, onion, garlic and jalapeno pepper.
Stir in the vinegar, lime juice, olive oil and red pepper sauce.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Makes 2 cups.
Preparation:
5 minutes, plus.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over crumbs.
Add chips and coconut in layers.
Pour milk over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; add onions and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup and rice.
Mix with broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine in order given.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before removing from sheet.
Can be doubled.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a bowl, place flour and make a well.
Drop remaining ingredients into well (a drop or 2 of yellow food coloring may be added to milk for more color).
Mix with fork, then fingers, until it forms a very stiff dough.
Roll out on floured surface until very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes; cut as you desire, then spread noodles out and use or let dry for 2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Simmer	1
cup	strawberries
and
2/3	cup water for 3 minutes.
Mix
1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Stir
until
smooth;
add to strawberry mixture. Boil. Stir until clear and thick. Add red food coloring. Cool.
Pour 4 cups
fresh
strawberries
in
baked pie shell. Pour cooled syrup on top. Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine water and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add rest of ingredients all at once.
Boil slowly, stirring until mixture has thickened, about 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Coat with salt and pepper.
Brown in large saucepan with onions.
Add garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and catsup.
Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Dissolve flour in small amount of water.
Add to mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook in electric frypan at 325°.
Fry potatoes in oil to cover bottom of pan until halfway done.
Add squash to potatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until onion and bell pepper are done, stirring frequently.
Add sausage.
When sausage is done, cover the top with cheese until melted.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugars, add eggs and hot water.
Add flour, soda,
salt,
oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls and
bake
at
for 8 minutes or until brown.
Can be baked in a
9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 15 minutes and cut into bars. Can
substitute
1 cup currants or raisins for chocolate chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and cover with topping (topping recipe follows).

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over All-Bran and let stand.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat.
Add buttermilk and beat. Sift flour, soda and salt.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: *Substitute for Buttermilk:
1 cup skim milk and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk and melted oleo.
Blend in chopped nuts.
Spread in lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour over entire batter the 1 3/4 cups hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom. Invert squares of pudding on dessert plates.
Dip sauce from pan over each square.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: delicious moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350°.

title: clobbered chicken
directions: Do not salt chicken.
Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Add cheese and melt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until bubbling hot.

title: swedish mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and mash potatoes. Mix in butter, milk, parsley and sour cream; mash until smooth (no lumps), then add green onions to top of potatoes in baking dish.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes, until golden on top.

title: oriental casserole with tuna
directions: Butter casserole.
Place 1/2 noodles in bottom.
Pour in mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. May be served with soy sauce.
(One can bean sprouts may be added.)

title: curried fruit
directions: Heat oven to
Melt
butter; add sugar and curry. Drain and dry
fruits;
place
in 2 quart casserole in layers; add butter mixture.
Bake
40 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Serve warm. Makes 12 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour, salt and pepper into meat; heat fat and brown on each side, then add onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
May be cooked inside oven or covered on top of stove.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Mix.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: holly farms potatoes
directions: Mix the flour, Parmesan cheese and all the spices thoroughly in a large Ziploc bag.
Cut the potatoes into 4 wedges each and shake well in mixture.
Lay in single layer in buttered pan. Bake at 350° to 400° until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn potatoes halfway through baking time.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put ground peppers and sure jell in pan. Combine food coloring and vinegar and add to pepper mixture.
Boil mixture hard for 1 minute. Add sugar and boil hard for 2 minutes. Spoon into hot jars and seal. Makes 4 pt.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Allow ice cream (fudge twirl, vanilla, chocolate or experiment with your own flavor) to begin melting while making crust.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in square 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Or microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and continue cooking on High another 4 to 6 minutes longer, until peaches are tender.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until mixture is set in the center.

title: no bake twix cookies
directions: Melt chips; remove from heat and stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat together first four ingredients until very well mixed-several minutes.
Use electric mixer.
Pour into 7 or 8-inch round glass baking dish.
Bake in 350 oven for 30 minutes.
Leave oven on, set cake out to cool for 15 minutes.
Then mix 8 oz sour cream, 3 Tbsp sugar 1 1/2 tsp vanilla.
Pour over top of cake. Sprinkle with cinnamon, and put back in oven for 10 minutes.
Cool and then chill in refrigerator.

title: honey pecan pie
directions: Pour honey into an iron skillet and bring to a boil.
Beat eggs well and slowly add to hot honey, stirring constantly.
Add salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and put butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: alaska wild berry cobbler
directions: Place the butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Slash a few times to make it melt faster.
Place in heated oven to let it melt.
Remove from oven.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, the flour, baking powder and the salt.
Add enough milk to make a thin batter.
Pour this mixture over butter in the pan.
Spread the berries over dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the fruit.
Pour on 2 cups water and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic olives
directions: Do Ahead:
Turn olives and their juice into a quart jar with tight fitting lid.
Add vinegar and rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Shake well.
Refrigerate several days, shaking jar occasionally.

title: grilled pork spareribs
directions: Season ribs with granulated garlic, black pepper, lemon pepper and salt.
In saucepan, add mustard greens, vinegar, peppers and 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil, then strain.
Next, add remainder of ingredients and 1 cup of water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour sauce over ribs, add 1/2 cup of water to pan with tight lid and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian salad
directions: In a large bowl, marinate with French dressing the lettuce, onions and green beans.
Alternate layers of other ingredients, reserving 1 egg to be sliced for decorating top.
Pour over entire salad 1 cup Thousand Island dressing or 1 cup caviar dressing (mayonnaise and 1 jar caviar).
Marinate lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue beans with ground beef
directions: Saute onion until clear.
Add ground beef and brown.
Mix all other ingredients in a large pan or crock-pot.
Add ground beef to this and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes until flavors go through.
Can be doubled for large gatherings.

title: pan sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Freeze in 1 pound packages.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip, then mashed avocado mixed with lemon juice; spread sour cream mixed with taco seasoning; spread mayonnaise on next.
Top with onions, tomato and cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix together sugar, salt and cornstarch until well blended.
Add scalded milk, very slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook mixture in top of double boiler, stirring often, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and butter until well blended.
Pour into baked pastry shell; top with meringue made from 4 egg whites.

title: chocolate lust
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts by hand.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°, until lightly brown. Cool.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Cook pie shells as directed.
Then let cool.
Put nuts, coconut and butter on top of stove.
Cook on medium heat until brown.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and cream cheese with mixer.
Then add Cool Whip.
Layer in pie shells, starting with cream cheese mixture and alternating layers.
Then pour caramel on top when finished. Then sprinkle with a little bit of coconut mixture on top.
(Put 2 layers on each pie.)
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and let set for 24 hours.

title: chicken breasts(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle seasoning on both sides of chicken (amount depending on how spicy you like).
On underside of chicken pieces, put a couple dots of margarine, then cover each piece with 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons of wheat bran.
Put coated side of chicken down on microwave-safe platter or baking pan.
Repeat margarine and bran on top side of chicken.
Cover with wax paper or plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
May take longer if chicken was frozen.
Turn dish once during cooking.
Don't overcook.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Cut egg roll wraps into fourths.
Combine cream cheese with desired amount of green onion.
Place small ball of cream cheese in the center of the wrap.
Fold into triangle and fold corner to corner in fan shape.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa; add 1/3 cup milk and mix (quite stiff).
Add eggs and set aside.
In saucepan, bring to a boil 1 1/2 cups milk, butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until thick and smooth. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with the juicy mangoes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour in greased loaf pan at 375°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix sour cream with taco seasoning package.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with sour cream mixture.
Add lettuce, then chopped tomato.
Top with cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and vegetable oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and 2 cups bananas.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli and layer in casserole dish.
Melt cheese in milk.
Cook rice and melt butter.
Spoon rice between broccoli stems.
Pour melted cheese over rice.
Mix melted butter and crackers; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot rice beef
directions: Fry ground beef with onions.
Cook beef, onions, bouillon and celery with soups and hot water.
Wash rice in cold water and dry. Add to other ingredients.
Rice is uncooked.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: grape ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze in a gallon freezer.

title: southern cracker fried chicken
directions: Place buttermilk in shallow dish; combine crackers, garlic, sage, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake.
Mix thoroughly. Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk.
Place one or two pieces at a time in a bag.
Shake to coat.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: In a saucepan, heat pineapple with juice and Jello until boiling. Pour into mixing bowl and fold in Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Refrigerate several hours or overnight until set.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind all ingredients and add 1/2 cup canning salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and squeeze out all the juice as possible.
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil, then add dry ingredients. Can in sterile jars and seal.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, oil, ginger and garlic until sugar is dissolved.
Fold each wing tip under cut end to form a triangle.
Place chicken wings in a plastic bag set in a bowl.
Pour soy mixture over wings; seal bag. Chill in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight, turning over once to redistribute marinade.

title: bourbon barbecued ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients except spareribs; let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
Place spareribs, meaty side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast uncovered in 325° oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Brush sauce over ribs.
Roast, turning and brushing frequently with sauce, until ribs are done, about 45 minutes longer.
Heat remaining sauce to boiling, stirring occasionally. Serve with ribs.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips; add rice cereal.
Coat well.
Spread and press in a 10-inch pie pan for crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture; stir just until batter is moist.
Pour into 2 (1 pound) greased coffee cans; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: butter pecan fingers
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll out finger length and size.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Dust while hot with powdered sugar.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange cranberry cake
directions: Drain the pineapple. Combine flour, sugar and soda. Stir in dates and almonds. Combine pineapple with eggs, cranberry sauce, oil and orange peel. Stir in dry mixture.
Pour into baking dish or an 8 x 4-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Prepare the
starter
in
a
glass,
pottery or plastic container.	Store
the
covered
container in the refrigerator when starter is done.
The starter may smell quite sour, and a liquid may form
on its surface, but this is normal.
Stir the starter before
each
use.	After using the starter, be sure 1 cup is left in container.
If you want to keep starter indefinitely, add 1
cup milk, 1 cup flour and 3/4 cup sugar to this remaining starter
every
week to 10 days.
Do not use starter for 24 hours after feeding it.

title: broccoli with macaroni(broccoli di zita)
directions: Wash
and
clean
broccoli.
Cut
thick
stems
through center and then across, making
pieces
from
each piece of broccoli. In large saucepan bring 4 quarts of salted water to a boil. Plunge pasta and
broccoli
into water and boil until desired tenderness is reached.
"Al dente" is best and usually is 10 minutes.
When done, lift out broccoli-macaroni mix with slotted spoon and place in large bowl.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the water the pasta was cooked in.
Pour
the oil and water on top of the broccoli-macaroni mixture
and
toss lightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste;
serve
immediately.
Makes
4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat well; bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Put water, margarine and oil in pan.
Bring to boil, set aside to cool.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Add cooled mixture to this.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can ice or just sift with powdered sugar.

title: ethan's cornflake baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Crush cornflakes in sealed

gallon size plastic bag with rolling pin. Open the bag and add the flour, paprika, onion powder, sage and salt and pepper. Seal bag and shake until well blended. Pour the milk into a shallow bowl. Rinse the chicken pieces. Dip one piece in the milk, drop into the bag of cornflake mix and shake until the chicken is well coated. Place the chicken skin side up in an ungreased baking pan. Repeat until all pieces are coated. Discard any leftover coating. Bake for 50 minutes or until done.

title: turkey supreme glamour salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well.
Turn into bowl lined with salad greens.
Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: cold bean salad
directions: Blend well and pour over bean mixture; stir well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes a large quantity; keeps well.

title: date-carrot bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon juice, rind and grated carrots; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to carrot mixture and blend.
Add diced dates; mix until dates are well coated.
Generously grease an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or three 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Spoon batter into prepared pan or pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (small loaves) or 45 to 50 minutes (large loaf).

title: blueberry and spice bread pudding
directions: Place bread and berries in a buttered 9-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly over the bread, completely moistening the bread and berries.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: strawberry smoothy
directions: Pour strawberry nectar in the blender.
Add banana.
Add ice, then blend on high speed for 3 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix well.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour rice mixture on top of chicken.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; drain.
Add rice, salt and water; mix well.
Place 1/2 of chopped cabbage in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Put remaining cabbage over meat. Pour soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup tube pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and orange peel.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.

title: easy whole wheat bread
directions: Combine 2 cups wheat flour, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Heat in a saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°), the yeast, milk and oil.
Add egg and warm liquid to flour mixture. Beat half minute at low speed, 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in 1 cup whole wheat flour and 3 to 4 cups unbleached or all-purpose flour to form soft dough.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Put
through
cookie press on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into ball and roll in crushed pecans.

title: lo-fat french fries
directions: Scrub the potatoes. Don't peel.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips. Place potatoes in plastic bag with oil. Shake to coat.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange potatoes in single layer and bake 30 minutes until golden brown at 450°; turn every 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve with vinegar (optional).

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Can be prepared for baking up to 4 hours ahead.
Put the potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Add all the ingredients, with the exception of the French fried onions.
Beat at medium speed until well blended, then at high speed until light and fluffy. Add salt and pepper, if needed.
Spoon into a greased 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with the French fried onions and bake, uncovered, at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into a 2-quart casserole. Top with shredded cheese. Place in preheated 350° oven and bake 45 minutes.
(Cover with aluminum foil during earlier baking period.)

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into greased, lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; cool in pan.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
In a bowl, mix together soup, sour cream, squash, 3/4 cup of stuffing mix and the carrots and onion together.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix remaining butter and stuffing together and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
If rolling, add flour and powder in proportion.
Or drop by spoonfuls. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, EXCEPT SHRIMP, and stir until thoroughly combined. Stir shrimp in last so that there will still be pieces of shrimp. Serve with dipping size Fritos. Chill for 2 hours or more.

title: ma-maw black's blueberry crunch
directions: Grease lightly 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread undrained pineapple in bottom of pan. Spread blueberries over pineapple in bottom of pan. Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over berries. Spread cake mix over this. Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix. Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans over this. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until cake is done. After 25 minutes, cut for juice to come through.

title: hot artichoke appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and finely chop. Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add Parmesan cheese and garlic salt and again mix well.
Pour into rectangular ovenproof dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatin over cold milk; let stand 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Process until blended.
Arrange chocolate chips in bottom of crust.
Pour in gelatin mixture; sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus until tender, reserving liquid.
Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add asparagus liquid to evaporated milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into flour mixture. Blend until smooth.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Add beaten egg and milk to dry ingredients, stirring lightly.
Drop a teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into hot deep fat (360°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until a golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of small glass dipped in water.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: red cabbage
directions: Wash and remove outer leaves of cabbage.
Remove core and slice.
Peel and slice onion.
Peel and core apples.
Toss together.
Add rest of ingredients to mixture.
Simmer in oleo 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Thicken slightly with small amount of cornstarch by using some of the juice to mix with cornstarch. Make paste and add gradually to cabbage while stirring.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: In microwave-safe casserole dish, combine all ingredients except shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring at least twice during cooking.
Add Cheddar cheese, mix and microwave on High 5 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir.
Cheddar cheese should be melted and blended into sauce.
If not, put back in microwave at 2 minutes cooking time, until melted.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cool with cold running water.
Mix sugar with vinegar to help melt, and combine rest of ingredients.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
You can substitute pickle juice or red wine vinegar for the cider vinegar.
This is great for a large family gathering or party.
(Will make 1 gallon.)

title: parmesan party popcorn(appetizer)
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Drizzle melted margarine over popcorn.
Sprinkle with cheese and Italian seasoning; toss to coat well.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: my lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add the cold water, then the drained pineapple, cottage cheese and pecans. Mix well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or a large mold and chill until set.

title: vodka cream sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in saucepan; add garlic; fry well.
Add tomatoes and cook for 20 minutes.
Add red pepper flakes.
Add bay leaf and vodka and mix well.
Cook 5 minutes, then add heavy cream and mix well, stirring until all blended.
Cook 5 more minutes, then lower heat.
Let cook over low heat about 20 minutes, then pour over penne and serve.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Place Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream cheese in pan and heat until combined; add sausage.
Place in small crock pot to keep warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a pan.
Stir until clear on medium to medium-high heat.
When clear, boil until it spins a thread when dropped from the spoon, approximately 45 minutes. (Cook to 230° or until it threads.)
Add peanuts.
Boil until peanuts turn brown, 8 to 9 minutes.
Quickly stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour onto clean, ungreased cookie sheet and spread.

title: easy microwave caramel corn
directions: In large paper grocery bag, place popped popcorn.
In a 2- quart bowl, mix brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Put in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir; heat again for 1 minute. Stir and a third time, heat for 1 minute and stir.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour into bag over popcorn.
Shake vigorously.
Put bag and all into the microwave and heat for 30 seconds.
Remove and shake.
Heat another 30 seconds. Remove and shake and heat for a third time for 30 seconds.
Pour out onto wax paper or open grocery bag to dry.
Break up and store in airtight bowl.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything, except the cheese, in a large bowl.
Put in an oiled (with butter or olive oil) 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put cheese on top.
Cook, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. This is good the next day, warmed up.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Remove seeds from pumpkin and wash in colander under warm water. Spread seeds on cookie sheet and sprinkle with salt (use more or less to taste).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until seeds are dry and crisp.
Remove pan from oven with potholders.
Set on heatproof surface until seeds cool. Store in airtight container.

title: sauerkraut noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Put aside.
Cut sausage into bite-size pieces and brown.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in 3 quart casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well. Put into Bundt cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: country baked chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in large baking dish. Arrange vegetables around chicken.
Add water to gravy mix, stirring with wire whisk until smooth. Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Stir sauce before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt butter, then sift sugar into butter.
Add condensed milk, pecans, coconut, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place balls in refrigerator, while you melt chocolate bark in microwave or double boiler.
When chocolate is melted and smooth, dip balls and let cool on wax paper.

title: rice salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
In saucepan, combine rice, water, syrup and salt.
Mix to moisten.
Bring quickly to a boil. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; let cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil, skin and bone chicken.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together except crackers; put into a casserole dish and add a layer of Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable loaf
directions: Combine
vegetables,
stuffing
mix
and broth in large saucepan;
add butter and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer
for
6 minutes.
Add stuffing mix and stir just to moisten.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Add turkey
and
eggs, mix well.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf
pan
and
bake
at
375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Mix with 1 can mushroom soup plus a can of water or milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in pretty glass bowl or Tupperware bowl in the order listed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps for days and days.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add onion, corn, mayonnaise, oil and egg; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 12 muffins.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry ground chuck until brown, drain.
Add onion soup mix, both soups and taco sauce.
Stir well, bring to a boil, then simmer and stir for about 10 minutes.
In long glass dish put half of mixture.
Add 1/2 of cheese, then layer mixture, then other 1/2 of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve with Tostitos chips with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: herbed salmon ball
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, onion, fines herbs, thyme and garlic; blend well.
Stir in salmon.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Shape into ball.
In small bowl, combine parsley and nuts.
Roll salmon ball in mixture to coat evenly.
Serve with assorted crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: chipped beef dip(really delicious)
directions: Blend together first 2 ingredients, then add the remainder. Prepare a day ahead and heat through prior to serving.
Sprinkle chopped, toasted nuts on top.
Serve with small chunks of bread or chips.

title: fruit supreme
directions: Drain peach and pineapple juices together.
Add pudding mix into the juices.
Mix well.
Add peaches and pineapple back into mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Add bananas and fresh sliced strawberries to this mixture the next day.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift meal, baking powder and salt together.
Pour enough hot water to make a stiff dough.
Add cracklins (boil cracklins to soften them, optional).
Mold into oval shapes (pones) and bake at 425° until brown.

title: graham wafer pie
directions: Cook and cool.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat 2 egg whites for meringue.
Put on pie.
Just before baking, put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Take melted margarine and add yolks.
Mix in powdered sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Bake cake according to directions and break into pieces.
Layer cake, then Cool Whip mixture, then crushed candy bars.
Repeat.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, cornstarch, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Cook for 5 minutes or until thick. Add sausage.
May be eaten plain or served over rice or noodles.

title: my 5 pound candy
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and Karo.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly until it forms a hard ball in cold water or use candy thermometer.
Then beat as long as possible, adding vanilla and nuts before pouring onto a greased cookie sheet or pan.
Cool and cut.
Immediately hide it or you may only have a pound or less left.

title: raymond's chipped beef gravy
directions: Melt margarine in cast-iron skillet.
Break chipped beef into small pieces, add to margarine.
Add flour and mix.
Add enough milk to fill pan.
Cook slowly, stirring often.
Serve over crumbled day old bread.
Great on a cold winter's morning!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Drain cooked spaghetti; add all ingredients.
Let set overnight or at least several hours before serving.
Mix well again before serving.
Good with fish and barbecue.

title: truck stop
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Don't drain grease.
Dice vegetables and saute with meat.
Turn often.
Serve when potatoes are done. Season to taste.
Can add Tabasco when cooked.
Serves 8 to 10. Grated cheese on top and eggs on side go great with this.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Brown crushed crackers in oleo in skillet.
Add part of cracker mixture to Veg-All mixture. Spread rest on top.
Bake in casserole dish until brown at 350°.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice and saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place scallops, wine and seasonings in a saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of the broth.
Make a white sauce with the remaining butter, flour, broth and cream.
Add scallops and mushrooms.
Spoon into buttered shells or baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs or seasoned dry stuffing mix.
Bake for 10 minutes until browned.

title: peanut butter pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar. Mix in milk, peanut butter and vanilla. Add Cool Whip and pour into crust. Drizzle with chocolate syrup and freeze. Take out 5 minutes before serving.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo and vanilla.
Cook until it is as thick as you want it.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Put meringue on pie and bake until brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add nuts if you like.

title: baklava
directions: Prepare Honey Syrup.
Mix nuts and spices.
Brush bottom and sides of jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) with some of the margarine.
Unfold filo leaves; cover with damp towel to prevent drying.
Carefully separate 1 leaf; place in pan, folding edges over to fit pan if necessary.
Brush lightly with margarine. Repeat 6 times.

title: maple pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add pork chops and brown, turning once to brown second side.
Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a medium saucepan over a low heat, combine onion, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili powder, pepper, maple syrup and water, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour the mixture over pork chops and bake covered for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes. Remove pork chops; cover and set aside.

title: citrus and rosemary grilled pork
directions: To make marinade, combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl with a whisk or a fork. Pat chops dry with paper towels and rub on seasonings of salt and pepper. Turn chops in marinade and let stand 15 minutes.

title: marbled colored easter eggs
directions: Mix all these together.
Eggs dipped in this mixture will have a pretty marbled coloring.

title: teriyaki pasta
directions: Can add pea pods and broccoli if wish.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash soup mix thoroughly.
Drain; place in large kettle. Cover with water.
Add salt; soak overnight.
Drain.
Add water and ham hocks or chopped ham.
Bring to boil; simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, lemon, red pepper and chili powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour or longer.
Serve with cornbread.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Blend oil, vanilla and egg with the apples.
Combine dry ingredients and mix in well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Yield: 9 servings, about 290 calories per serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Add sauce and beans, then heat.
Add cheese.
Put in casserole dish and top with biscuits that are separated in half.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Add Special K cereal.
Press into a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Melt 8 ounces milk chocolate and spread over top. Cool and cut into squares.
A good way to use up Easter bunnies and leftover chocolate.

title: easy cream puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a rolling boil.
While still on the heat add the flour and stir hard until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat.
Add 4 beaten eggs all at once and stir hard and patiently until dough is smooth.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 400°. Meanwhile, blend milk and pudding for filling. Add Kool Whip and refrigerate.
When puffs are cool, slit sideways, cutting off tops.
Fill with pudding mixture, replace top and dust with confectionary sugar.

title: creole sausage and rice bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine rice and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Spread mixture in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Combine eggs and next 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all of the ingredients; use about 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water for delicious hot chocolate.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until very thick and lemon colored.
Add water. Beat until very thick.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly, about 10 minutes, with electric mixer at highest speed.
Fold in extracts, sift flour and salt together.
Carefully fold into egg yolk mixture.

title: baba's jello cubes
directions: Spray dish or pan with Pam.
Dissolve Jell-O well; pour into dish or pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Kids like them real well.

title: garden chicken marengo
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Combine chicken and mushrooms in a shallow layer in a nonstick skillet; add olive oil.
Cook over high heat until mushrooms and chicken begin to brown on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 3 to 4 more minutes until sauce is thick.
Stir in tomatoes at last minute, only until heated through.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 4.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil to 235°. Beat until icing is ready to spread.
Add vanilla; stir well.

title: mississippi mud slide
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar and butter until well mixed.
Line bottom of pan with graham cracker mixture.
Save about 1/2 cup for topping.
Sprinkle walnut pieces over crackers as desired.
Save a few for top.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package (mix in large bowl).

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together the first 2 ingredients. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Fold in the flour, alternating (one cup at a
time) with the 7-Up (1/2 cup at a time), starting and ending with flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake begins to leave side of pan. This is a moist cake.

title: e-z pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs for 4 minutes.
Fold in pumpkin, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in dry mixture.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp and cucumber canapes
directions: Bring 4 cups of water to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain well; rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp; cover and chill.
Wash cucumbers; trim ends.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Scoop out center of each slice to, but not through, bottom.
Invert cucumbers on paper towels and let stand 30 minutes.
Place ham in a large skillet; add water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes on each side.
Drain.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add ham.
Pulse 10 times or until ham is chopped. Add cream cheese; pulse 10 times or until blended.
Spoon into a pastry bag fitted with a No. 5 tip; pipe into each cucumber slice. Top with shrimp; garnish, if desired.
Yield:
36 appetizer servings.

title: old-fashion cooked chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and melted Crisco.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat with mixer until creamy. Frost cooled cake.

title: dinardaraan (pork with blood)
directions: Cut pork into cubes; set aside, separating fat portion from meat.
Cut pork intestines and stomach approximately 1/2-inch long and simmer in separate pot for 1 hour.
Set aside.
Brown fat of pork; then add garlic.
Brown and add lean meat and cook for 1/2 hour or until meat is cooked.
Add bay leaves and 1/4 teaspoon of ground pepper.
