Add boiled internal organs and cook for another 20 minutes.
On a separate bowl, mix blood with 1/2 cup vinegar and a cup of water.
Add to the cooked meat, constantly stirring until blood is cooked or when its color turns to blackish color.
Add salt to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Mmm-good!

title: granola #3
directions: Baking Temperature: 225°.
Baking Time: 2 hours.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and cut a thin slice off top.
Scoop out potato and add all ingredients to the scooped out potato (except 1/4 cup cheese and paprika).
Mix together and spoon back into potato shells.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cut about 6 potatoes (medium size) into fourths and boil until soft.
Boil eggs with potatoes.
Place potatoes in serving dish.
Spread tuna on top of potatoes.
Slice eggs and place on top of tuna.
Cut tomatoes in fourths and place on top of eggs. Put olives over tomatoes (amount you desire).
Dice parsley and sprinkle over the entire salad.
Pour olive oil over salad to your liking.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil margarine, Karo and sugar 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Stir until well mixed into the popped corn.
Turn onto jelly roll pan and bake 1 hour at 200° stirring and turning every 20 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine the juice and grated rind of orange, melted shortening and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Add beaten egg.
Blend liquid into dry ingredients.
Stir only until the flour mixture is dampened, add chopped nuts and cranberries.
Pour into greased pan (8 1/2 x 4 x 3-inches).
Push batter into corners of pan.
Allow to stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight the celery, onion and dressing.
Whip cream cheese in food processor; add mayonnaise and seasonings to form right consistency for dip.
Add drained celery and onion.
Drain shrimp; rinse several times and blot shrimp. Mash thoroughly with silver fork.
Add to dip.
Add salt to taste.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Scald one cup of the cream in a double boiler.
Mix egg yolks, spices, flour, sugar and remaining cream and add slowly to the hot mixture.
Cook fifteen minutes.
Add raisins and vanilla.
When partly cooled, pour into a baked crust.
Cover with meringue made from stiffly beaten egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in a slow oven (300° to 350°).
Try one sometimes.
I bet you'll like it.

title: parmesan herb bread
directions: Mix spread, cheese, garlic and basil.
Spread on cut surfaces of bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil until lightly browned. Cut into slices.

title: berry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt the butter.
Combine all the ingredients together.
Mix well.
Wrap in wax paper overnight.
Slice off 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: half and half pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, milk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir well, then refrigerate until it cools down a little.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream, mixing well.
Stir in pecans and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: rice dressing
directions: Combine all of the ingredients to the ground beef and cook until done, then combine with rice.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: You crack some eggs and put them in a bowl.
Put some honey and oil, oil first.
Then dry milk powder.
Then cook them and eat them!

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg, green pepper and onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until done.
tags: tomato sauce with bits of tomatoes

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes, remove and add kisses.
Rebake 2 to 3 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together. Set aside. Mix the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and black pepper. Mix well and pour over corn mixture. Stir in. Place in airtight container and refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: muenster pie
directions: Place salami in pie shell to cover bottom.
Layer cheese and repeat salami-cheese layers until 3/4 full.
Pour beaten eggs into shell.
Cover with top layer of crust.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Cool a few minutes in pan.
Turn out onto cooling rack.
Cool thoroughly before storing; wrap with plastic.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Add spices to water.
Bring water to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea immediately.
Brew for 4 minutes.
Strain.
Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices.
To reheat, do not re-boil.
Heat on low heat until hot.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken and mushrooms in oil until chicken is slightly browned.
Add all ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil and stir in rice.
Cover and let stand 7 minutes before opening.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, red pepper, green pepper and salt. Let stand overnight; drain and rinse.
Add pepper, cornstarch, celery seed, turmeric, sugar, and vinegar.
Add to zucchini and simmer for 50 minutes.
Pour into sterile jars and seal at once.

title: tuna sandwich
directions: Mix all together, spread on buttered bread.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Cook until a small amount forms a soft ball (234° to 240°) when dropped in cold water.

Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and cook the rest until it forms a hard ball (250° to 265°) when dropped in cold water. Pour the 1/2 cup of syrup slowly over the stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating; add the remaining syrup.
Add nuts and vanilla; keep beating until mass thickens and becomes heavy.
Pour into a buttered pan; cut when cold, or drop with a teaspoon onto a buttered surface or wax paper.

title: broccoli carnival
directions: Trim off large	leaves	of broccoli.
Remove tough ends and wash broccoli
thoroughly.	Make lengthwise slits in thick stalks. Arrange broccoli
in
steaming
racks
with stalks to center of racks.
Place
over
boiling water;
cover and steam 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in serving dish.

title: favorite sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in vanilla and cardamon.
Stir in 1 cup of blueberries.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the brown sugar and top with remaining batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix with fork and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage weckel
directions: In skillet or Dutch oven-type pan, cook butter and onion until tender on low heat so it doesn't burn.
Add cabbage, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cover and cook until done on low heat so it doesn't burn.
In water, cook noodles until done.
Drain and add to cabbage mixture and serve.
(Cook noodles while cabbage mixture is cooking so both will be ready at same time.)

title: mud slide dip
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Place water, egg and beans in a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth.
Add to onion.
Stir in chili powder, salt and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
When cool, stir in mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: crunchy apple cobbler(low-fat)
directions: Layer the oats in the bottom of an 8-inch square nonstick pan. Add the apple slices.

Pour the apple juice on top and sprinkle with raisins, cinnamon and cloves. Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove the foil. Cover the top of the apples with crunchy cereal and bake an additional 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash 10 to 15 minutes. Drain and mash 1 cup.
Combine 1 cup mashed squash and egg.
Stir well. Combine flour, meal, baking powder and salt.
Stir. Add squash mixture and onion. Stir until blended.
Drop squash mixture by level tablespoon into hot oil. Cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towel. Yields 2 dozen.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple (reserve 2 tablespoons liquid).
Mix juice, Heinz 57 sauce and honey and pour over chicken.
Bake an additional 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Arrange pineapple over chicken and bake 10 minutes longer.
The boneless chicken breasts are great in this recipe.

title: string bean casserole
directions: In a quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce until smooth. Mix in beans, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: marble angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per directions on package folding gelatin into 1/3 of the batter.
Alternately spoon batters into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batters to marble.
Bake on lowest rack at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is golden brown and springs back when lightly pressed.
Turn cake upside down over funnel or bottle to cool down.
Remove from pan. Frost with whipped topping, if desired.

title: plant food fun
directions: You will need one clean plastic flowerpot and plastic flower (carnations, perhaps).

title: brie wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a food processor and process until creamy.
Add flour, cayenne, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix, pushing on and off until a very soft dough forms.
Transfer the dough to a plate and shape into a log about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap tightly in plastic and refrigerate overnight.

title: parmesan oven chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, cheese and parsley in a bowl.
Mix well. Dip chicken in butter and roll in stuffing mixture.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Do not turn chicken while cooking.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches
directions: Put
all
ingredients
in
quart
crock-pot
or slow cooker.
Mix
well.
Cover;
cook on High at 300° for 8 hours. With
wire
whisk, stir mixture until meat is shredded.
Serve on poor boy buns with sliced onion and dill pickles.
Makes 12 sandwiches.
To
cook on top of range, use 6 quart Dutch oven. Add 1 cup water.
Simmer 3 hours.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Lightly grease crock-pot. Toss macaroni and oil. Add remaining ingredients. Stir; cover and cook on low 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: potato cookies
directions: Combine molasses and shortening; add hot potatoes.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to molasses mixture.
Then add chopped, cooked raisins or prunes and stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet and bake for about 12 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line large flat pan with tortillas.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over tortillas.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Slice bananas into blender.
Whirl 1 minute, until smooth. Pour into a punch bowl.
Place strawberries in blender and whirl until smooth.
Pour into the punch bowl.
Add lemonade and water to punch bowl and stir until well blended.
Pour in ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with mint sprig.
Makes a scant 3 quarts.

title: indian corn
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add green pepper and onion that has been cooked until soft and drained.
Add tomato soup, corn, salt, pepper and cooked noodles, if desired.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in 8 x 12 Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack. Yield: one 10-inch cake.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Put crackers and dry ingredients into gallon size zipper bag and shake well.
Pour oil into bag and shake well again.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Then turn and shake bag, repeating.
When all is mixed well, pour into airtight tin or container.
Good as a snack out of hand, also on soup.

title: pink punch
directions: Add water to lemonade to make 8 cups.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and egg, then add flour with milk.
Blend well.
Add jam by folding in gently.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350°.
When done, spread extra jam between layers.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let set 20 minutes.
Cream together the remaining ingredients.
Add oatmeal mixture. Bake at 350° on cookie sheet. Spread topping on cake while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, cheese, 1/2 cup cereal, soup, celery, onion, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining cereal and butter, mixing well. Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain
corn and beans.	Mix all ingredients except last 3 together.
Add salt to taste.
Sprinkle crushed crackers and grated cheese over top.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake in a
x
13-inch
casserole dish, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Halve avocados; scoop pulp into a large bowl and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients to avocado and stir to blend. Makes abut 4 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Some nuts and chocolate chips may be added if you like.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a large bowl, combine the egg whites, sugar, cookie crumbs, walnuts and coconut. Mix well. Pour into the unbaked pie crust. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Lower the temperature to 350 degrees and continue baking for another 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is set and the top is crispy.
Allow the pie to cool completely before slicing. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip. This pie is so rich that you can probably get 10 servings rather than 8.

title: mexican layered salad
directions: Layer in order:
beans, meat, sour cream, guacamole, onions, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. With pastry blender, cut shortening into flour mixture until coarse crumbs form.
Sprinkle water over flour mixture, one tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly after each addition.
Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Knead until smooth, about 3 minutes. Roll half dough into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into 12 (3 x 3-inch) squares.
Heat 1 1/2 inches of oil to 400°.
Fry squares, turning with slotted spoon.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and drizzle with honey.
Repeat with remaining dough.

title: light and flaky never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. In small
bowl, beat together the egg, cold water and vinegar. Add this
to
flour
mixture.
Chill
1/2 hour.
Will make two pies, top and bottom crust.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and put in a casserole dish.
Mix in green beans, soup and milk.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and top with tater tots.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in slow cooker.
Add peanuts and potato chips.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper.
When firm, cut into bars.
Dark or white chocolate may be used.
Toasted pecans and coconut can be substituted for peanuts and chips.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Mix all first 6 ingredients together and then add Barbecue Rub to taste.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Blend cheese with 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion together with cream cheese. Make 8 triangles of rolled crescent dough.
Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture in the middle.
Pull corners to center and seal edge.
Brush top with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle with crushed croutons and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skillet meatball dinner
directions: Mix ground beef with next 3 ingredients.
Divide into small meatballs (a little larger than walnuts).
Brown in skillet turning to brown all sides.
Add rice, stirring until rice begins to brown slightly.
Add carrots, soy sauce and 2 cups water, stirring to blend well.
Cover and cook on low heat until rice is tender (about 30 minutes).

title: pork pie
directions: Roll out the pastry and line a pie casserole, reserving enough pastry to form a lid.
Cut the meat into small cubes and season with pepper and salt.
Dried mixed herbs may also be added.
Fill the pie with the cut meat and sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Dampen the edges of the pie and place the top in position.
Leave a hole in the center.
Brush the top of the pie with a little beaten egg yolk.
Bake in a moderate oven for 2 to 2
1/2 hours.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut steak into strips, approximately 1/2 x 2 inches each. Place steak in large, rectangular dish and cover with Italian dressing and beer (approximately 2 cups dressing to each cup beer).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and orange through coarse grinder; add sugar and chopped nuts.

title: southwestern cowpoke chili
directions: Saute jalapenos, beef, onions and garlic until meat loses red color.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until you've finished the first case of beer.

title: caramel turtle fudge brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together. Spread half the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Remove cake mix from oven.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top, then spread caramel mixture over that.
Top with remaining half of cake mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Batter will be thick.
Blend remaining 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until the top has a brown glaze and pulls from the sides of the pan.
Cool and cut as you would brownies.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix egg into Ricotta cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make layers of pasta, sauce, meat, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Make several layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked northern beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Cover with water and boil until when you blow on the beans the skins come off.
Add soda.
Let bubble; drain and rinse.
Put in baking dish.
Add other ingredients.
Cover top with bacon.
Bake at 400° until it boils.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Finish baking 2 more hours at 300°.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Melt the margarine.
Mix the brown sugar, oatmeal, peanut butter, white syrup and vanilla. Add melted margarine.
Mix well. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir constantly.
Remove from fire.
Let cool until hand can be held on bottom of pan.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into wax paper-lined pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: monster munch
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler and stir until smooth. Mix everything in with chocolate; drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator until cool.

title: wild strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together and press in 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pseudo crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Make cakes as you normally do for crab cakes.
Fry medium-high until golden brown. Turn on other side (not you, the cakes).
Fry until done.
Now taste.
Surprise.

title: chocolate mess
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Break up 1/2 cooled cake into punch bowl.
Spread 1/2 pudding over cake and then 1/2 whipped topping over pudding.
Put three frozen Heath bars in blender or food processor and break into small pieces.
Sprinkle over whipped topping.
Repeat with rest of cake, pudding, whipped topping and remaining Heath bars.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl; toss quickly until cereal is completely covered with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time. Press mixture evenly into pan with piece of waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares (48 squares).

title: hot tomato dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with Doritos or taco chips.

title: pita bread chips
directions: Pry apart pita bread and spread with melted oleo.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Cut in quarters and put on cookie sheet in oven at 250° for 30 minutes or until crisp.
Serve cold.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook, debone and slice the chicken into large slices.
Cook the broccoli and arrange it in a flat baking dish with the chicken on top.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and spread over the chicken.
Cooked mushrooms can be added to the sauce.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit and fiber cereal
directions: Mix together and store in Tupperware container.

title: jalapeno cheese spread
directions: Mix together until it is creamed.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into loaf.

title: pecan delights
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Stir.
Add pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, potato chips and walnuts. After mixed well, gradually blend in flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until edges are brown.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Mix all together and blend 1/2 recipe at a time.
Mix all together and it is ready to serve.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (moderate). Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bring salted water to a boil. Add macaroni and cook, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain. Cover bottom of casserole with half the macaroni.

Combine cheese; sprinkle half the mixture over macaroni in casserole. Repeat layers. Combine beaten eggs with milk, onion and seasonings. Pour over macaroni and cheese. Sprinkle top with corn flake crumbs. Set casserole in a pan of hot water. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown and almost set in center.
Servings for 6.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well and add milk and butter.
Cook until thickened and add vanilla.
Cool and put in baked pie shell.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, except vodka.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Cool overnight.
Strain.
Add vodka.
Let set 4 weeks.

title: millie's three cheese tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions, drain reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Put tortellini back in cooking pot.
Add cream cheese and butter.
Mix together over low heat until tortellini is well covered with cheese - butter mixture adding cooking water if needed to make a creamy sauce.
Take off heat and add parsley.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with mozzarella.
Bake at 450° until cheese is melted and golden, 5 - 10 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Pour in 1 3/4 to 2 cups warm water and mix.
Mix with hands until soft.
Take a ball of soft dough, pat back and forth (or roll out with rolling pin) and pull until flat and round.
Put one cup Crisco oil in pan; heat until hot.
Cook dough until brown on both sides.
Serve with chili beans or can be used as dessert with honey.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll out on floured board. Cut into small rounds. Bake at 375° until light brown, about 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: *Or 2 cups sour cream.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs, and place in an 8-inch square (approximately) greased casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Soften cheese and margarine. Grate cheese into large mixing bowl. Add softened margarine. Mix well by hand. Add flour, Rice Krispies and pepper. Mix well.
Form into dough mixture.
Pinch cheese dough and form into balls. Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten ball with fork. Cook approximately 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: "no peek" stew
directions: Layer meat, carrots, potatoes and onions in a large oven-safe dish with lid (or you may use crock-pot).
Pour V-8 juice over meat and vegetables; sprinkle with tapioca pudding.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 325° oven for 4 hours.
Do not remove lid or open oven door.

title: cheese olive puffs
directions: Blend grated cheese with butter or margarine. Add flour, salt and paprika. Mix. Wrap 1 teaspoon cheese mixture around each stuffed olive. Arrange on a baking sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan; add onions and cook until tender. Blend in flour, salt and nutmeg, stirring over low heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring until sauce thickens.
Add cheese and spinach; heat thoroughly.
Meanwhile, mix bread crumbs with melted butter. Place spinach in serving dish and sprinkle with bread crumb mixture.
Serves 8.

title: chicken filling(fills 8 crepes)
directions: Stew breast 20 minutes.
Debone; remove fat and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix all ingredients gently.
Do not cook or heat. Ready to stuff crepes.
Serves 8.

title: white icing
directions: Mix flour and milk. Cook until thick.
Cool completely.
Cream remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Stir into cold mixture. Beat until light and fluffy.

title: citrus spritzer
directions: Spoon lemonade concentrate into a drinking glass.
Pour about 1/4 cup club soda into glass.
Stir to dissolve lemonade.
Stir in remaining club soda.
Add ice cubes, lemon and lime slices.
Serve cold.
Makes 1 serving.

title: coconut filling for layer cake
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt. Add milk; bring to a boil.
Beat egg white until stiff. Add to mixture slowly and cook a few more minutes.
Spread between layers of cake and over top and sides.

title: spinach puff hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook spinach and drain, squeezing out extra juices.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Especially good if taken out of the oven and allowed to stand for a few minutes before serving.
Spear with toothpicks and dip into Lemon Mayonnaise.

title: untossed molded salad
directions: Start the day before.
Place the lettuce in a bowl.
Add on top, in layers, the celery, onions and peas.
Cover with the mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate.

title: beef mushroom soup
directions: Heat butter in pan and saute mushrooms until light brown. Strain out mushrooms and set aside.
Heat cooking liquid; add flour and cook until thick.
Gradually stir in broth until blended.
Add onion, bay, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened.
Turn down heat and add half and half.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Strain.
Add mushrooms to broth.
Heat and serve.

title: squirrel bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter and add 1 egg.
Mix well.
Pat mixture into 9 x 12-inch cake pan which has been well greased.
Press into this 1 cup chopped nuts.
Beat together the egg whites, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into small squares before cool.
These improve with age.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add all but the whipped cream. Blend well.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Freeze until solid.
Cut into squares and serve on crisp lettuce with cherries as garnish.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, forming small balls about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes, then transfer to foil or waxed paper to cool completely.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: lemon-blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine Jell-O pie filling, sugar, 1/4 cup water and egg in saucepan. Blend thoroughly. Add remaining water and cook as directed on package.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Measure 1 cup filling, cover surface with wax paper. Chill completely in refrigerator, about 2 hours. Pour remaining filling into pie shell.

title: barbecued smoked brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with celery, onion and garlic salt.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Cover and refrigerate (overnight is best).

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Dissolve Jell-O, 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.
In saucepan, combine egg, margarine, juice, sugar and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Prepare package of Dream Whip and fold into cooled topping mixture.
Spread over set Jell-O and top with cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: peppernuts(german cookie)
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, fruit and nuts and stir.
Add soda dissolved in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and blend into batter.
(This is stiff so you'll have to mix with hands.)
Chill until real stiff.
Rol lout into small logs about the size of your finger.
Chill again, then cut and place on sheet, cut side up and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and let set several hours in refrigerator.

title: non-alcoholic egg nog
directions: Assemble 1 group of people in assorted sizes, shapes and personalities, measure accurately:
1 cup friendly words, 1 cup courtesy and patience and 2 heaping cups of understanding.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Place chops in a slow cooker.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add onions, pepper, celery and tomatoes.
Combine ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and bouillon. Pour over chops and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low heat for 5 to 6 hours.
Mix cornstarch and water until smooth and stir in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high heat for 30 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and mix.
Add remaining ingredients together and mix.
Put in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add other ingredients in given order, mixing with each item thoroughly as added.
Drop by spoonful out on buttered tin.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs and beat 3 minutes.
Drain off 1/2 cup juice from fruit cocktail and add the rest to mixture.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in batter. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over top before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken lemon stew
directions: In a 4-quart pan, combine 2 1/2 cups water, cardamom, rose water, lemon juice, saffron and salt.
On high heat, bring the mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Dissolve the flour in the 1/2 cup water, then add to the liquid slowly with continuous mixing.
When mixture thickens, add chicken pieces.
Cover and let cook until chicken pieces are tender.

title: oatmeal snickerdoodle drops
directions: Bake in 375° oven.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup granulated sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle lightly over each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend all together.
Add 3 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil, then take it off the burner. Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well, then add Special K.
Stir until all cereal is coated.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: 3 day easy coconut cake
directions: Mix the cake according to directions on box. Bake in 2 cake layers and cool. Split in 4 layers. Mix 2 packages fresh coconut with sour cream and sugar. Set aside 1/2 cup of this mixture for later use. Spread the rest between layers. Now mix the 1/2 cup mixture with the whipped topping; spread on top and sides. Refrigerate 3 days in an airtight container before cutting.

title: sauteed peppers
directions: Combine the vegetables in a 2-quart casserole. Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and microwave on high 4-6 minutes or until the peppers are crisp-tender. Stir once or twice during cooking. Makes 3-4 servings.

title: chicken and corn soup
directions: Combine chicken with chicken stock, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour, skimming the surface as necessary. Remove the chicken and cool.
Pick the meat from the bones and cut into small pieces.
Strain broth through a fine sieve.
Add the corn, parsley (1 tablespoon) and 1 cup cooked egg noodles to the broth.
Return to simmer and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese. Mix with fruit.
Add whipped cream to mixture.
Pour into mold or tray.
Freeze until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix milk, soup and Cheez Whiz together and pour over broccoli. Add instant rice and dot with butter.
You can add cooked hamburger to this also to make a one dish meal.
Cook 45 minutes on 375°.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken in shallow glass dish.
Cover.
Vent.
Microwave at 100% power 2 to 4 minutes, rotate halfway through cooking time. Do not overcook.
Cut in small pieces.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing package, Ramen flavor packets, vinegar, oil and a little juice from water chestnuts.
Combine with cabbage, drained water chestnuts and celery.
Marinate overnight.
Add Ramen noodles (crushed by hand), almonds and sesame seed before serving.
Mix well.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: frozen lime pie
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add condensed milk and evaporated milk; beat until smooth.
With mixer on medium speed, add lime juice and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 10 to 15 minutes, then serve.

title: penne with vodka and tomato cream sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil and butter until translucent. Add tomatoes and simmer until the juice from the tomatoes is reduced by half, stirring frequently. Add cream, vodka and peppers. Simmer until thickened. Season with salt and pepper. Toss with pasta and top with Parmesan cheese and chives. Serves 4.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes, onion and cheese with salt and pepper to taste.
Dot each layer with butter. Cover with milk until it shows at corners.
Sprinkle with parsley or paprika.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix in double boiler.
Serve hot in chafing dish with assorted crackers.

title: date nut pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, white sugar and water.
Cook until thick (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and add nuts and lemon juice.
Cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar (1/2 cup white), cinnamon, soda, baking powder and ginger.
Drain pineapple well; save juice. In medium bowl, mix pineapple, brown sugar, egg substitute, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir pineapple mixture, carrots, zucchini and raisins into flour mixture.
Stir until moist.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until toothpick is clean.
When cool, you can glaze with powdered sugar and pineapple juice.

title: boy scout goulash
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Add abut 1/4 cup vegetable oil. Layer potatoes and carrots.
Make ground beef into 4 to 6 patties and place on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place thick sliced onion on top.
Cover and let cook at low temperature for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bumble berry pie
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Whisk together egg, vinegar and water, and sprinkle over dry ingredients; toss.
Add more water if needed, 1 Tbsp. at a time, until dough can be formed into a ball.
Divide into 4 portions.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out 2 portions to fit 2 9-inch pie pans.
Prepare filling by stirring together the berries, rhubarb, apples, sugar, flour and 2 Tbsp. lemon juice.
If using frozen berries, thaw partially before mixing.
Divide mixture evenly into the 2 pie pans.
Roll remaining portions of dough to fit pies and place over filling.
Seal and flute edges.
Beat egg yolk and water together and brush over pies.
Cut slits in the top crust.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: boiled okra
directions: Wash okra.
Place in saucepan.
Cover with water; add vinegar and bacon grease.
Boil until tender.
Drain.

title: 10 minute microwave bread and butter pickles(1 quart plus)
directions: Mix all in microwave-safe bowl (3-quart size).
Cook on High 7 to 10 minutes.
Stop and stir twice during cooking time.
Pour into hot clean jar and refrigerate.
Works equally well with just plain white onions and no pickles.

title: cherry jubilee ring
directions: Drain cherries and reserve 3/4 cup syrup.
Combine syrup, jelly and sherry.
Bring just to boil and remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add cherries and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add nuts.
Chill in 3 cup ring overnight.
Unmold on greens.
Makes 6 servings.
